var book = {
	"name": "1 Samuel",
	"numChapters": 31,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>There was a certain man from Ramathaim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7214A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7214A\"></sup> a Zuphite<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7214B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7214B\"></sup> from the hill country<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7214C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7214C\"></sup> of Ephraim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7214D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7214D\"></sup> whose name was Elkanah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7214E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7214E\"></sup> son of Jeroham, the son of Elihu, the son of Tohu, the son of Zuph, an Ephraimite.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He had two wives;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7215F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7215F\"></sup> one was called Hannah and the other Peninnah. Peninnah had children, but Hannah had none.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Year after year<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7216G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7216G\"></sup> this man went up from his town to worship<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7216H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7216H\"></sup> and sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> Almighty at Shiloh,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7216I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7216I\"></sup> where Hophni and Phinehas, the two sons of Eli,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7216J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7216J\"></sup> were priests of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Whenever the day came for Elkanah to sacrifice,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7217K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7217K\"></sup> he would give portions of the meat to his wife Peninnah and to all her sons and daughters.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7217L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7217L\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But to Hannah he gave a double portion<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7218M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7218M\"></sup> because he loved her, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had closed her womb.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7218N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7218N\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had closed Hannah’s womb, her rival kept provoking her in order to irritate her.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7219O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7219O\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>This went on year after year. Whenever Hannah went up to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, her rival provoked her till she wept and would not eat.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7220P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7220P\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Her husband Elkanah would say to her, “Hannah, why are you weeping? Why don’t you eat? Why are you downhearted? Don’t I mean more to you than ten sons?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7221Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7221Q\"></sup>”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Once when they had finished eating and drinking in Shiloh, Hannah stood up. Now Eli the priest was sitting on his chair by the doorpost of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s house.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7222R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7222R\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>In her deep anguish<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7223S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7223S\"></sup> Hannah prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, weeping bitterly.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And she made a vow,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7224T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7224T\"></sup> saying, “<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> Almighty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7224U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7224U\"></sup>, if you will only look on your servant’s misery and remember<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7224V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7224V\"></sup> me, and not forget your servant but give her a son, then I will give him to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for all the days of his life,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7224W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7224W\"></sup> and no razor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7224X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7224X\"></sup> will ever be used on his head.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>As she kept on praying to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, Eli observed her mouth.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Hannah was praying in her heart, and her lips were moving but her voice was not heard. Eli thought she was drunk",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and said to her, “How long are you going to stay drunk? Put away your wine.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“Not so, my lord,” Hannah replied, “I am a woman who is deeply troubled.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7228Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7228Y\"></sup> I have not been drinking wine or beer; I was pouring<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7228Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7228Z\"></sup> out my soul to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Do not take your servant for a wicked woman; I have been praying here out of my great anguish and grief.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7229AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7229AA\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Eli answered, “Go in peace,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7230AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7230AB\"></sup> and may the God of Israel grant you what you have asked of him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7230AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7230AC\"></sup>”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>She said, “May your servant find favor in your eyes.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7231AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7231AD\"></sup>” Then she went her way and ate something, and her face was no longer downcast.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7231AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7231AE\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Early the next morning they arose and worshiped before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and then went back to their home at Ramah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7232AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7232AF\"></sup> Elkanah made love to his wife Hannah, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> remembered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7232AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7232AG\"></sup> her.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So in the course of time Hannah became pregnant and gave birth to a son.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7233AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7233AH\"></sup> She named<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7233AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7233AI\"></sup> him Samuel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7233AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7233AJ\"></sup> saying, “Because I asked the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for him.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When her husband Elkanah went up with all his family to offer the annual<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7234AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7234AK\"></sup> sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and to fulfill his vow,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7234AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7234AL\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Hannah did not go. She said to her husband, “After the boy is weaned, I will take him and present<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7235AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7235AM\"></sup> him before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and he will live there always.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“Do what seems best to you,” her husband Elkanah told her. “Stay here until you have weaned him; only may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> make good<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7236AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7236AN\"></sup> his word.” So the woman stayed at home and nursed her son until she had weaned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7236AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7236AO\"></sup> him.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>After he was weaned, she took the boy with her, young as he was, along with a three-year-old bull,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7237AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7237AP\"></sup> an ephah of flour and a skin of wine, and brought him to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at Shiloh.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>When the bull had been sacrificed, they brought the boy to Eli,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>and she said to him, “Pardon me, my lord. As surely as you live, I am the woman who stood here beside you praying to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>I prayed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7240AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7240AQ\"></sup> for this child, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has granted me what I asked of him.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So now I give him to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. For his whole life<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7241AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7241AR\"></sup> he will be given over to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” And he worshiped the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> there."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>Then Hannah prayed and said:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7242A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7242A\"></sup>“My heart rejoices<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7242B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7242B\"></sup> in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my horn<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7242C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7242C\"></sup> is lifted high.My mouth boasts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7242D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7242D\"></sup> over my enemies,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7242E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7242E\"></sup>for I delight in your deliverance.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“There is no one holy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7243F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7243F\"></sup> like<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7243G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7243G\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;there is no one besides you;there is no Rock<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7243H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7243H\"></sup> like our God.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“Do not keep talking so proudlyor let your mouth speak such arrogance,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7244I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7244I\"></sup>for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is a God who knows,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7244J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7244J\"></sup>and by him deeds<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7244K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7244K\"></sup> are weighed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7244L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7244L\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“The bows of the warriors are broken,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7245M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7245M\"></sup>but those who stumbled are armed with strength.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7245N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7245N\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Those who were full hire themselves out for food,but those who were hungry<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7246O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7246O\"></sup> are hungry no more.She who was barren<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7246P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7246P\"></sup> has borne seven children,but she who has had many sons pines away.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brings death and makes alive;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7247Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7247Q\"></sup>he brings down to the grave and raises up.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7247R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7247R\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sends poverty and wealth;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7248S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7248S\"></sup>he humbles and he exalts.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7248T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7248T\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He raises<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7249U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7249U\"></sup> the poor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7249V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7249V\"></sup> from the dust<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7249W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7249W\"></sup>and lifts the needy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7249X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7249X\"></sup> from the ash heap;he seats them with princesand has them inherit a throne of honor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7249Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7249Y\"></sup>“For the foundations<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7249Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7249Z\"></sup> of the earth are the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s;on them he has set the world.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He will guard the feet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7250AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7250AA\"></sup> of his faithful servants,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7250AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7250AB\"></sup>but the wicked will be silenced in the place of darkness.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7250AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7250AC\"></sup>“It is not by strength<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7250AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7250AD\"></sup> that one prevails;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>those who oppose the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will be broken.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7251AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7251AE\"></sup>The Most High will thunder<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7251AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7251AF\"></sup> from heaven;the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will judge<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7251AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7251AG\"></sup> the ends of the earth.“He will give strength<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7251AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7251AH\"></sup> to his kingand exalt the horn<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7251AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7251AI\"></sup> of his anointed.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then Elkanah went home to Ramah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7252AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7252AJ\"></sup> but the boy ministered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7252AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7252AK\"></sup> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> under Eli the priest.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Eli’s sons were scoundrels; they had no regard<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7253AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7253AL\"></sup> for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now it was the practice<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7254AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7254AM\"></sup> of the priests that, whenever any of the people offered a sacrifice, the priest’s servant would come with a three-pronged fork in his hand while the meat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7254AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7254AN\"></sup> was being boiled",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and would plunge the fork into the pan or kettle or caldron or pot. Whatever the fork brought up the priest would take for himself. This is how they treated all the Israelites who came to Shiloh.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But even before the fat was burned, the priest’s servant would come and say to the person who was sacrificing, “Give the priest some meat to roast; he won’t accept boiled meat from you, but only raw.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>If the person said to him, “Let the fat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7257AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7257AO\"></sup> be burned first, and then take whatever you want,” the servant would answer, “No, hand it over now; if you don’t, I’ll take it by force.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>This sin of the young men was very great in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s sight, for they were treating the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s offering with contempt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7258AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7258AP\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But Samuel was ministering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7259AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7259AQ\"></sup> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—a boy wearing a linen ephod.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7259AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7259AR\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Each year his mother made him a little robe and took it to him when she went up with her husband to offer the annual<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7260AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7260AS\"></sup> sacrifice.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Eli would bless Elkanah and his wife, saying, “May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> give you children by this woman to take the place of the one she prayed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7261AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7261AT\"></sup> for and gave to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” Then they would go home.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was gracious to Hannah;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7262AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7262AU\"></sup> she gave birth to three sons and two daughters. Meanwhile, the boy Samuel grew<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7262AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7262AV\"></sup> up in the presence of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Now Eli, who was very old, heard about everything<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7263AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7263AW\"></sup> his sons were doing to all Israel and how they slept with the women<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7263AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7263AX\"></sup> who served at the entrance to the tent of meeting.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So he said to them, “Why do you do such things? I hear from all the people about these wicked deeds of yours.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>No, my sons; the report I hear spreading among the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s people is not good.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>If one person sins against another, God may mediate for the offender; but if anyone sins against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who will<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7266AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7266AY\"></sup> intercede<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7266AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7266AZ\"></sup> for them?” His sons, however, did not listen to their father’s rebuke, for it was the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s will to put them to death.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And the boy Samuel continued to grow<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7267BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7267BA\"></sup> in stature and in favor with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and with people.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7267BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7267BB\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Now a man of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7268BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7268BC\"></sup> came to Eli and said to him, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: ‘Did I not clearly reveal myself to your ancestor’s family when they were in Egypt under Pharaoh?",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>I chose<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7269BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7269BD\"></sup> your ancestor out of all the tribes of Israel to be my priest, to go up to my altar, to burn incense,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7269BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7269BE\"></sup> and to wear an ephod<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7269BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7269BF\"></sup> in my presence. I also gave your ancestor’s family all the food offerings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7269BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7269BG\"></sup> presented by the Israelites.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Why do you scorn my sacrifice and offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7270BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7270BH\"></sup> that I prescribed for my dwelling?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7270BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7270BI\"></sup> Why do you honor your sons more than me by fattening yourselves on the choice parts of every offering made by my people Israel?’",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>“Therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, declares: ‘I promised that members of your family would minister before me forever.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7271BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7271BJ\"></sup>’ But now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> declares: ‘Far be it from me! Those who honor me I will honor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7271BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7271BK\"></sup> but those who despise<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7271BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7271BL\"></sup> me will be disdained.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7271BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7271BM\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The time is coming when I will cut short your strength and the strength of your priestly house, so that no one in it will reach old age,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7272BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7272BN\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>and you will see distress<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7273BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7273BO\"></sup> in my dwelling. Although good will be done to Israel, no one in your family line will ever reach old age.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7273BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7273BP\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Every one of you that I do not cut off from serving at my altar I will spare only to destroy your sight and sap your strength, and all your descendants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7274BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7274BQ\"></sup> will die in the prime of life.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“‘And what happens to your two sons, Hophni and Phinehas, will be a sign<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7275BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7275BR\"></sup> to you—they will both die<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7275BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7275BS\"></sup> on the same day.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7275BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7275BT\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>I will raise up for myself a faithful priest,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7276BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7276BU\"></sup> who will do according to what is in my heart and mind. I will firmly establish his priestly house, and they will minister before my anointed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7276BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7276BV\"></sup> one always.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Then everyone left in your family line will come and bow down before him for a piece of silver and a loaf of bread and plead,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7277BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7277BW\"></sup> “Appoint me to some priestly office so I can have food to eat.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7277BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7277BX\"></sup>”’”"
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>The boy Samuel ministered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7278A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7278A\"></sup> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> under Eli. In those days the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was rare;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7278B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7278B\"></sup> there were not many visions.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7278C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7278C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>One night Eli, whose eyes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7279D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7279D\"></sup> were becoming so weak that he could barely see,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7279E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7279E\"></sup> was lying down in his usual place.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The lamp<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7280F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7280F\"></sup> of God had not yet gone out, and Samuel was lying down in the house<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7280G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7280G\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, where the ark<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7280H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7280H\"></sup> of God was.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> called Samuel.Samuel answered, “Here I am.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7281I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7281I\"></sup>”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And he ran to Eli and said, “Here I am; you called me.”But Eli said, “I did not call; go back and lie down.” So he went and lay down.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Again the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> called, “Samuel!” And Samuel got up and went to Eli and said, “Here I am; you called me.”“My son,” Eli said, “I did not call; go back and lie down.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now Samuel did not yet know<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7284J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7284J\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: The word<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7284K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7284K\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had not yet been revealed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7284L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7284L\"></sup> to him.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>A third time the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> called, “Samuel!” And Samuel got up and went to Eli and said, “Here I am; you called me.”Then Eli realized that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was calling the boy.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So Eli told Samuel, “Go and lie down, and if he calls you, say, ‘Speak, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for your servant is listening.’” So Samuel went and lay down in his place.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came and stood there, calling as at the other times, “Samuel! Samuel!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7287M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7287M\"></sup>”Then Samuel said, “Speak, for your servant is listening.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Samuel: “See, I am about to do something in Israel that will make the ears of everyone who hears about it tingle.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7288N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7288N\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>At that time I will carry out against Eli everything<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7289O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7289O\"></sup> I spoke against his family—from beginning to end.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>For I told him that I would judge his family forever because of the sin he knew about; his sons blasphemed God, and he failed to restrain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7290P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7290P\"></sup> them.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Therefore I swore to the house of Eli, ‘The guilt of Eli’s house will never be atoned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7291Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7291Q\"></sup> for by sacrifice or offering.’”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Samuel lay down until morning and then opened the doors of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. He was afraid to tell Eli the vision,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>but Eli called him and said, “Samuel, my son.”Samuel answered, “Here I am.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“What was it he said to you?” Eli asked. “Do not hide<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7294R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7294R\"></sup> it from me. May God deal with you, be it ever so severely,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7294S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7294S\"></sup> if you hide from me anything he told you.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So Samuel told him everything, hiding nothing from him. Then Eli said, “He is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; let him do what is good in his eyes.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7295T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7295T\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7296U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7296U\"></sup> Samuel as he grew<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7296V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7296V\"></sup> up, and he let none<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7296W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7296W\"></sup> of Samuel’s words fall to the ground.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And all Israel from Dan to Beersheba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7297X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7297X\"></sup> recognized that Samuel was attested as a prophet of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7297Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7297Y\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> continued to appear at Shiloh, and there he revealed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7298Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7298Z\"></sup> himself to Samuel through his word."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>And Samuel’s word came to all Israel.Now the Israelites went out to fight against the Philistines. The Israelites camped at Ebenezer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7299A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7299A\"></sup> and the Philistines at Aphek.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7299B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7299B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The Philistines deployed their forces to meet Israel, and as the battle spread, Israel was defeated by the Philistines, who killed about four thousand of them on the battlefield.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When the soldiers returned to camp, the elders of Israel asked, “Why<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7301C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7301C\"></sup> did the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> bring defeat on us today before the Philistines? Let us bring the ark<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7301D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7301D\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s covenant from Shiloh,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7301E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7301E\"></sup> so that he may go with us<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7301F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7301F\"></sup> and save us from the hand of our enemies.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So the people sent men to Shiloh, and they brought back the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> Almighty, who is enthroned between the cherubim.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7302G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7302G\"></sup> And Eli’s two sons, Hophni and Phinehas, were there with the ark of the covenant of God.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s covenant came into the camp, all Israel raised such a great shout<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7303H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7303H\"></sup> that the ground shook.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Hearing the uproar, the Philistines asked, “What’s all this shouting in the Hebrew<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7304I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7304I\"></sup> camp?”When they learned that the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had come into the camp,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>the Philistines were afraid.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7305J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7305J\"></sup> “A god has come into the camp,” they said. “Oh no! Nothing like this has happened before.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>We’re doomed! Who will deliver us from the hand of these mighty gods? They are the gods who struck<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7306K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7306K\"></sup> the Egyptians with all kinds of plagues<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7306L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7306L\"></sup> in the wilderness.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Be strong, Philistines! Be men, or you will be subject to the Hebrews, as they<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7307M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7307M\"></sup> have been to you. Be men, and fight!”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So the Philistines fought, and the Israelites were defeated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7308N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7308N\"></sup> and every man fled to his tent. The slaughter was very great; Israel lost thirty thousand foot soldiers.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The ark of God was captured, and Eli’s two sons, Hophni and Phinehas, died.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7309O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7309O\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>That same day a Benjamite<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7310P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7310P\"></sup> ran from the battle line and went to Shiloh with his clothes torn and dust<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7310Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7310Q\"></sup> on his head.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When he arrived, there was Eli<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7311R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7311R\"></sup> sitting on his chair by the side of the road, watching, because his heart feared for the ark of God. When the man entered the town and told what had happened, the whole town sent up a cry.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Eli heard the outcry and asked, “What is the meaning of this uproar?”The man hurried over to Eli,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>who was ninety-eight years old and whose eyes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7313S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7313S\"></sup> had failed so that he could not see.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He told Eli, “I have just come from the battle line; I fled from it this very day.”Eli asked, “What happened, my son?”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The man who brought the news replied, “Israel fled before the Philistines, and the army has suffered heavy losses. Also your two sons, Hophni and Phinehas, are dead,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7315T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7315T\"></sup> and the ark of God has been captured.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7315U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7315U\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When he mentioned the ark of God, Eli fell backward off his chair by the side of the gate. His neck was broken and he died, for he was an old man, and he was heavy. He had led<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7316V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7316V\"></sup> Israel forty years.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7316W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7316W\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>His daughter-in-law, the wife of Phinehas, was pregnant and near the time of delivery. When she heard the news that the ark of God had been captured and that her father-in-law and her husband were dead, she went into labor and gave birth, but was overcome by her labor pains.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>As she was dying, the women attending her said, “Don’t despair; you have given birth to a son.” But she did not respond or pay any attention.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>She named the boy Ichabod,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7319X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7319X\"></sup> saying, “The Glory<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7319Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7319Y\"></sup> has departed from Israel”—because of the capture of the ark of God and the deaths of her father-in-law and her husband.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>She said, “The Glory<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7320Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7320Z\"></sup> has departed from Israel, for the ark of God has been captured.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7320AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7320AA\"></sup>"
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>After the Philistines had captured the ark of God, they took it from Ebenezer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7321A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7321A\"></sup> to Ashdod.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7321B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7321B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then they carried the ark into Dagon’s temple and set it beside Dagon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7322C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7322C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When the people of Ashdod rose early the next day, there was Dagon, fallen<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7323D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7323D\"></sup> on his face on the ground before the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>! They took Dagon and put him back in his place.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But the following morning when they rose, there was Dagon, fallen on his face on the ground before the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>! His head and hands had been broken<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7324E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7324E\"></sup> off and were lying on the threshold; only his body remained.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>That is why to this day neither the priests of Dagon nor any others who enter Dagon’s temple at Ashdod step on the threshold.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7325F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7325F\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s hand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7326G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7326G\"></sup> was heavy on the people of Ashdod and its vicinity; he brought devastation<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7326H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7326H\"></sup> on them and afflicted them with tumors.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7326I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7326I\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When the people of Ashdod saw what was happening, they said, “The ark of the god of Israel must not stay here with us, because his hand is heavy on us and on Dagon our god.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So they called together all the rulers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7328J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7328J\"></sup> of the Philistines and asked them, “What shall we do with the ark of the god of Israel?”They answered, “Have the ark of the god of Israel moved to Gath.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7328K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7328K\"></sup>” So they moved the ark of the God of Israel.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But after they had moved it, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s hand was against that city, throwing it into a great panic.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7329L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7329L\"></sup> He afflicted the people of the city, both young and old, with an outbreak of tumors.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So they sent the ark of God to Ekron.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7330M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7330M\"></sup>As the ark of God was entering Ekron, the people of Ekron cried out, “They have brought the ark of the god of Israel around to us to kill us and our people.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So they called together all the rulers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7331N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7331N\"></sup> of the Philistines and said, “Send the ark of the god of Israel away; let it go back to its own place, or it will kill us and our people.” For death had filled the city with panic; God’s hand was very heavy on it.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Those who did not die<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7332O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7332O\"></sup> were afflicted with tumors, and the outcry of the city went up to heaven."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>When the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had been in Philistine territory seven months,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>the Philistines called for the priests and the diviners<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7334A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7334A\"></sup> and said, “What shall we do with the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>? Tell us how we should send it back to its place.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They answered, “If you return the ark of the god of Israel, do not send it back to him without a gift;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7335B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7335B\"></sup> by all means send a guilt offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7335C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7335C\"></sup> to him. Then you will be healed, and you will know why his hand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7335D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7335D\"></sup> has not been lifted from you.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The Philistines asked, “What guilt offering should we send to him?”They replied, “Five gold tumors and five gold rats, according to the number<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7336E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7336E\"></sup> of the Philistine rulers, because the same plague<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7336F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7336F\"></sup> has struck both you and your rulers.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Make models of the tumors<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7337G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7337G\"></sup> and of the rats that are destroying the country, and give glory<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7337H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7337H\"></sup> to Israel’s god. Perhaps he will lift his hand from you and your gods and your land.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Why do you harden<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7338I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7338I\"></sup> your hearts as the Egyptians and Pharaoh did? When Israel’s god dealt harshly with them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7338J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7338J\"></sup> did they<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7338K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7338K\"></sup> not send the Israelites out so they could go on their way?",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“Now then, get a new cart<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7339L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7339L\"></sup> ready, with two cows that have calved and have never been yoked.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7339M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7339M\"></sup> Hitch the cows to the cart, but take their calves away and pen them up.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Take the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and put it on the cart, and in a chest beside it put the gold objects you are sending back to him as a guilt offering. Send it on its way,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>but keep watching it. If it goes up to its own territory, toward Beth Shemesh,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7341N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7341N\"></sup> then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has brought this great disaster on us. But if it does not, then we will know that it was not his hand that struck us but that it happened to us by chance.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So they did this. They took two such cows and hitched them to the cart and penned up their calves.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>They placed the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on the cart and along with it the chest containing the gold rats and the models of the tumors.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then the cows went straight up toward Beth Shemesh, keeping on the road and lowing all the way; they did not turn to the right or to the left. The rulers of the Philistines followed them as far as the border of Beth Shemesh.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now the people of Beth Shemesh were harvesting their wheat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7345O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7345O\"></sup> in the valley, and when they looked up and saw the ark, they rejoiced at the sight.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The cart came to the field of Joshua of Beth Shemesh, and there it stopped beside a large rock. The people chopped up the wood of the cart and sacrificed the cows as a burnt offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7346P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7346P\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The Levites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7347Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7347Q\"></sup> took down the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, together with the chest containing the gold objects, and placed them on the large rock.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7347R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7347R\"></sup> On that day the people of Beth Shemesh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7347S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7347S\"></sup> offered burnt offerings and made sacrifices to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The five rulers of the Philistines saw all this and then returned that same day to Ekron.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>These are the gold tumors the Philistines sent as a guilt offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—one each<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7349T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7349T\"></sup> for Ashdod, Gaza, Ashkelon, Gath and Ekron.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And the number of the gold rats was according to the number of Philistine towns belonging to the five rulers—the fortified towns with their country villages. The large rock on which the Levites set the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is a witness to this day in the field of Joshua of Beth Shemesh.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But God struck down<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7351U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7351U\"></sup> some of the inhabitants of Beth Shemesh, putting seventy of them to death because they looked<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7351V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7351V\"></sup> into the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. The people mourned because of the heavy blow the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had dealt them.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And the people of Beth Shemesh asked, “Who can stand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7352W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7352W\"></sup> in the presence of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, this holy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7352X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7352X\"></sup> God? To whom will the ark go up from here?”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then they sent messengers to the people of Kiriath Jearim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7353Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7353Y\"></sup> saying, “The Philistines have returned the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Come down and take it up to your town.”"
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum mid-paragraph\">7 </span><sup class=\"versenum mid-paragraph\">1 </sup>So the men of Kiriath Jearim came and took up the ark<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7354A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7354A\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. They brought it to Abinadab’s<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7354B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7354B\"></sup> house on the hill and consecrated Eleazar his son to guard the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The ark remained at Kiriath Jearim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7355C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7355C\"></sup> a long time—twenty years in all.Then all the people of Israel turned back to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7355D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7355D\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So Samuel said to all the Israelites, “If you are returning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7356E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7356E\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with all your hearts, then rid<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7356F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7356F\"></sup> yourselves of the foreign gods and the Ashtoreths<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7356G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7356G\"></sup> and commit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7356H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7356H\"></sup> yourselves to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and serve him only,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7356I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7356I\"></sup> and he will deliver<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7356J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7356J\"></sup> you out of the hand of the Philistines.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So the Israelites put away their Baals and Ashtoreths, and served the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> only.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Samuel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7358K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7358K\"></sup> said, “Assemble all Israel at Mizpah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7358L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7358L\"></sup> and I will intercede<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7358M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7358M\"></sup> with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for you.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When they had assembled at Mizpah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7359N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7359N\"></sup> they drew water and poured<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7359O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7359O\"></sup> it out before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. On that day they fasted and there they confessed, “We have sinned against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” Now Samuel was serving as leader<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7359P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7359P\"></sup> of Israel at Mizpah.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When the Philistines heard that Israel had assembled at Mizpah, the rulers of the Philistines came up to attack them. When the Israelites heard of it, they were afraid<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7360Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7360Q\"></sup> because of the Philistines.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>They said to Samuel, “Do not stop crying<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7361R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7361R\"></sup> out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God for us, that he may rescue us from the hand of the Philistines.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Samuel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7362S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7362S\"></sup> took a suckling lamb and sacrificed it as a whole burnt offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. He cried out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on Israel’s behalf, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> answered him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7362T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7362T\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>While Samuel was sacrificing the burnt offering, the Philistines drew near to engage Israel in battle. But that day the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> thundered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7363U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7363U\"></sup> with loud thunder against the Philistines and threw them into such a panic<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7363V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7363V\"></sup> that they were routed before the Israelites.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The men of Israel rushed out of Mizpah and pursued the Philistines, slaughtering them along the way to a point below Beth Kar.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Samuel took a stone<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7365W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7365W\"></sup> and set it up between Mizpah and Shen. He named it Ebenezer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7365X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7365X\"></sup> saying, “Thus far the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has helped us.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So the Philistines were subdued<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7366Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7366Y\"></sup> and they stopped invading Israel’s territory. Throughout Samuel’s lifetime, the hand of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was against the Philistines.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The towns from Ekron<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7367Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7367Z\"></sup> to Gath that the Philistines had captured from Israel were restored to Israel, and Israel delivered the neighboring territory from the hands of the Philistines. And there was peace between Israel and the Amorites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7367AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7367AA\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Samuel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7368AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7368AB\"></sup> continued as Israel’s leader<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7368AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7368AC\"></sup> all<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7368AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7368AD\"></sup> the days of his life.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>From year to year he went on a circuit from Bethel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7369AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7369AE\"></sup> to Gilgal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7369AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7369AF\"></sup> to Mizpah, judging<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7369AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7369AG\"></sup> Israel in all those places.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But he always went back to Ramah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7370AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7370AH\"></sup> where his home was, and there he also held court<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7370AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7370AI\"></sup> for Israel. And he built an altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7370AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7370AJ\"></sup> there to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>When Samuel grew old, he appointed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7371A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7371A\"></sup> his sons as Israel’s leaders.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The name of his firstborn was Joel and the name of his second was Abijah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7372B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7372B\"></sup> and they served at Beersheba.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7372C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7372C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But his sons<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7373D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7373D\"></sup> did not follow his ways. They turned aside<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7373E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7373E\"></sup> after dishonest gain and accepted bribes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7373F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7373F\"></sup> and perverted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7373G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7373G\"></sup> justice.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So all the elders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7374H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7374H\"></sup> of Israel gathered together and came to Samuel at Ramah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7374I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7374I\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They said to him, “You are old, and your sons do not follow your ways; now appoint a king<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7375J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7375J\"></sup> to lead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7375K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7375K\"></sup> us, such as all the other nations<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7375L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7375L\"></sup> have.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But when they said, “Give us a king<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7376M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7376M\"></sup> to lead us,” this displeased<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7376N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7376N\"></sup> Samuel; so he prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> told him: “Listen<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7377O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7377O\"></sup> to all that the people are saying to you; it is not you they have rejected,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7377P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7377P\"></sup> but they have rejected me as their king.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7377Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7377Q\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>As they have done from the day I brought them up out of Egypt until this day, forsaking<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7378R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7378R\"></sup> me and serving other gods, so they are doing to you.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now listen to them; but warn them solemnly and let them know<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7379S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7379S\"></sup> what the king who will reign over them will claim as his rights.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Samuel told<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7380T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7380T\"></sup> all the words of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to the people who were asking him for a king.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He said, “This is what the king who will reign over you will claim as his rights: He will take<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7381U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7381U\"></sup> your sons and make them serve<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7381V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7381V\"></sup> with his chariots and horses, and they will run in front of his chariots.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7381W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7381W\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Some he will assign to be commanders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7382X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7382X\"></sup> of thousands and commanders of fifties, and others to plow his ground and reap his harvest, and still others to make weapons of war and equipment for his chariots.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He will take your daughters to be perfumers and cooks and bakers.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He will take the best of your<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7384Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7384Y\"></sup> fields and vineyards<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7384Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7384Z\"></sup> and olive groves and give them to his attendants.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7384AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7384AA\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He will take a tenth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7385AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7385AB\"></sup> of your grain and of your vintage and give it to his officials and attendants.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Your male and female servants and the best of your cattle and donkeys he will take for his own use.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He will take a tenth of your flocks, and you yourselves will become his slaves.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When that day comes, you will cry out for relief from the king you have chosen, but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will not answer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7388AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7388AC\"></sup> you in that day.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7388AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7388AD\"></sup>”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But the people refused<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7389AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7389AE\"></sup> to listen to Samuel. “No!” they said. “We want<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7389AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7389AF\"></sup> a king<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7389AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7389AG\"></sup> over us.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then we will be like all the other nations,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7390AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7390AH\"></sup> with a king to lead us and to go out before us and fight our battles.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When Samuel heard all that the people said, he repeated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7391AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7391AI\"></sup> it before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> answered, “Listen<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7392AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7392AJ\"></sup> to them and give them a king.”Then Samuel said to the Israelites, “Everyone go back to your own town.”"
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>There was a Benjamite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7393A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7393A\"></sup> a man of standing,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7393B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7393B\"></sup> whose name was Kish<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7393C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7393C\"></sup> son of Abiel, the son of Zeror, the son of Bekorath, the son of Aphiah of Benjamin.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Kish had a son named Saul, as handsome<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7394D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7394D\"></sup> a young man as could be found<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7394E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7394E\"></sup> anywhere in Israel, and he was a head taller<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7394F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7394F\"></sup> than anyone else.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now the donkeys<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7395G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7395G\"></sup> belonging to Saul’s father Kish were lost, and Kish said to his son Saul, “Take one of the servants with you and go and look for the donkeys.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So he passed through the hill<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7396H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7396H\"></sup> country of Ephraim and through the area around Shalisha,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7396I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7396I\"></sup> but they did not find them. They went on into the district of Shaalim, but the donkeys<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7396J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7396J\"></sup> were not there. Then he passed through the territory of Benjamin, but they did not find them.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When they reached the district of Zuph,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7397K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7397K\"></sup> Saul said to the servant who was with him, “Come, let’s go back, or my father will stop thinking about the donkeys and start worrying<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7397L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7397L\"></sup> about us.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But the servant replied, “Look, in this town there is a man of God;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7398M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7398M\"></sup> he is highly respected, and everything<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7398N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7398N\"></sup> he says comes true. Let’s go there now. Perhaps he will tell us what way to take.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Saul said to his servant, “If we go, what can we give the man? The food in our sacks is gone. We have no gift<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7399O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7399O\"></sup> to take to the man of God. What do we have?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The servant answered him again. “Look,” he said, “I have a quarter of a shekel of silver. I will give it to the man of God so that he will tell us what way to take.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>(Formerly in Israel, if someone went to inquire<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7401P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7401P\"></sup> of God, they would say, “Come, let us go to the seer,” because the prophet of today used to be called a seer.)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7401Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7401Q\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Good,” Saul said to his servant. “Come, let’s go.” So they set out for the town where the man of God was.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>As they were going up the hill to the town, they met some young women coming out to draw<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7403R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7403R\"></sup> water, and they asked them, “Is the seer here?”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“He is,” they answered. “He’s ahead of you. Hurry now; he has just come to our town today, for the people have a sacrifice<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7404S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7404S\"></sup> at the high place.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7404T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7404T\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>As soon as you enter the town, you will find him before he goes up to the high place to eat. The people will not begin eating until he comes, because he must bless<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7405U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7405U\"></sup> the sacrifice; afterward, those who are invited will eat. Go up now; you should find him about this time.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>They went up to the town, and as they were entering it, there was Samuel, coming toward them on his way up to the high place.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now the day before Saul came, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had revealed this to Samuel:",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“About this time tomorrow I will send you a man from the land of Benjamin. Anoint<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7408V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7408V\"></sup> him ruler<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7408W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7408W\"></sup> over my people Israel; he will deliver<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7408X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7408X\"></sup> them from the hand of the Philistines.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7408Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7408Y\"></sup> I have looked on my people, for their cry<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7408Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7408Z\"></sup> has reached me.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When Samuel caught sight of Saul, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “This<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7409AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7409AA\"></sup> is the man I spoke to you about; he will govern my people.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Saul approached Samuel in the gateway and asked, “Would you please tell me where the seer’s house is?”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“I am the seer,” Samuel replied. “Go up ahead of me to the high place, for today you are to eat with me, and in the morning I will send you on your way and will tell you all that is in your heart.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>As for the donkeys<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7412AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7412AB\"></sup> you lost three days ago, do not worry about them; they have been found. And to whom is all the desire<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7412AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7412AC\"></sup> of Israel turned, if not to you and your whole family line?”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Saul answered, “But am I not a Benjamite, from the smallest tribe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7413AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7413AD\"></sup> of Israel, and is not my clan the least<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7413AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7413AE\"></sup> of all the clans of the tribe of Benjamin?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7413AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7413AF\"></sup> Why do you say such a thing to me?”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Samuel brought Saul and his servant into the hall and seated them at the head of those who were invited—about thirty in number.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Samuel said to the cook, “Bring the piece of meat I gave you, the one I told you to lay aside.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So the cook took up the thigh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7416AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7416AG\"></sup> with what was on it and set it in front of Saul. Samuel said, “Here is what has been kept for you. Eat, because it was set aside for you for this occasion from the time I said, ‘I have invited guests.’” And Saul dined with Samuel that day.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>After they came down from the high place to the town, Samuel talked with Saul on the roof<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7417AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7417AH\"></sup> of his house.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>They rose about daybreak, and Samuel called to Saul on the roof, “Get ready, and I will send you on your way.” When Saul got ready, he and Samuel went outside together.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>As they were going down to the edge of the town, Samuel said to Saul, “Tell the servant to go on ahead of us”—and the servant did so—“but you stay here for a while, so that I may give you a message from God.”"
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>Then Samuel took a flask<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7420A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7420A\"></sup> of olive oil and poured it on Saul’s head and kissed him, saying, “Has not the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> anointed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7420B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7420B\"></sup> you ruler over his inheritance?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7420C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7420C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>When you leave me today, you will meet two men near Rachel’s tomb,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7421D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7421D\"></sup> at Zelzah on the border of Benjamin. They will say to you, ‘The donkeys<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7421E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7421E\"></sup> you set out to look for have been found. And now your father has stopped thinking about them and is worried<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7421F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7421F\"></sup> about you. He is asking, “What shall I do about my son?”’",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“Then you will go on from there until you reach the great tree of Tabor. Three men going up to worship God at Bethel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7422G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7422G\"></sup> will meet you there. One will be carrying three young goats, another three loaves of bread, and another a skin of wine.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They will greet you and offer you two loaves of bread,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7423H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7423H\"></sup> which you will accept from them.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“After that you will go to Gibeah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7424I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7424I\"></sup> of God, where there is a Philistine outpost.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7424J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7424J\"></sup> As you approach the town, you will meet a procession of prophets<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7424K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7424K\"></sup> coming down from the high place<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7424L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7424L\"></sup> with lyres, timbrels,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7424M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7424M\"></sup> pipes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7424N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7424N\"></sup> and harps<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7424O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7424O\"></sup> being played before them, and they will be prophesying.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7424P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7424P\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The Spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7425Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7425Q\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will come powerfully upon you, and you will prophesy with them; and you will be changed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7425R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7425R\"></sup> into a different person.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Once these signs are fulfilled, do whatever<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7426S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7426S\"></sup> your hand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7426T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7426T\"></sup> finds to do, for God is with<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7426U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7426U\"></sup> you.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“Go down ahead of me to Gilgal.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7427V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7427V\"></sup> I will surely come down to you to sacrifice burnt offerings and fellowship offerings, but you must wait seven<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7427W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7427W\"></sup> days until I come to you and tell you what you are to do.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>As Saul turned to leave Samuel, God changed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7428X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7428X\"></sup> Saul’s heart, and all these signs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7428Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7428Y\"></sup> were fulfilled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7428Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7428Z\"></sup> that day.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When he and his servant arrived at Gibeah, a procession of prophets met him; the Spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7429AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7429AA\"></sup> of God came powerfully upon him, and he joined in their prophesying.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7429AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7429AB\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When all those who had formerly known him saw him prophesying with the prophets, they asked each other, “What is this<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7430AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7430AC\"></sup> that has happened to the son of Kish? Is Saul also among the prophets?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7430AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7430AD\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>A man who lived there answered, “And who is their father?” So it became a saying: “Is Saul also among the prophets?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7431AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7431AE\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>After Saul stopped prophesying,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7432AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7432AF\"></sup> he went to the high place.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Now Saul’s uncle<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7433AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7433AG\"></sup> asked him and his servant, “Where have you been?”“Looking for the donkeys,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7433AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7433AH\"></sup>” he said. “But when we saw they were not to be found, we went to Samuel.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Saul’s uncle said, “Tell me what Samuel said to you.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Saul replied, “He assured us that the donkeys<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7435AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7435AI\"></sup> had been found.” But he did not tell his uncle what Samuel had said about the kingship.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Samuel summoned the people of Israel to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at Mizpah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7436AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7436AJ\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and said to them, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, says: ‘I brought Israel up out of Egypt, and I delivered you from the power of Egypt and all the kingdoms that oppressed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7437AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7437AK\"></sup> you.’",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But you have now rejected<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7438AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7438AL\"></sup> your God, who saves<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7438AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7438AM\"></sup> you out of all your disasters and calamities. And you have said, ‘No, appoint a king<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7438AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7438AN\"></sup> over us.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7438AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7438AO\"></sup> So now present<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7438AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7438AP\"></sup> yourselves before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by your tribes and clans.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When Samuel had all Israel come forward by tribes, the tribe of Benjamin was taken by lot.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then he brought forward the tribe of Benjamin, clan by clan, and Matri’s clan was taken.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7440AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7440AQ\"></sup> Finally Saul son of Kish was taken. But when they looked for him, he was not to be found.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So they inquired<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7441AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7441AR\"></sup> further of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “Has the man come here yet?”And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “Yes, he has hidden himself among the supplies.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>They ran and brought him out, and as he stood among the people he was a head taller<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7442AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7442AS\"></sup> than any of the others.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Samuel said to all the people, “Do you see the man the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has chosen?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7443AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7443AT\"></sup> There is no one like<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7443AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7443AU\"></sup> him among all the people.”Then the people shouted, “Long live<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7443AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7443AV\"></sup> the king!”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Samuel explained<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7444AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7444AW\"></sup> to the people the rights and duties<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7444AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7444AX\"></sup> of kingship.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7444AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7444AY\"></sup> He wrote them down on a scroll and deposited it before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Then Samuel dismissed the people to go to their own homes.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Saul also went to his home in Gibeah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7445AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7445AZ\"></sup> accompanied by valiant men<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7445BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7445BA\"></sup> whose hearts God had touched.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But some scoundrels<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7446BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7446BB\"></sup> said, “How can this fellow save us?” They despised him and brought him no gifts.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7446BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7446BC\"></sup> But Saul kept silent."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>Nahash<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7447A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7447A\"></sup> the Ammonite went up and besieged Jabesh Gilead.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7447B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7447B\"></sup> And all the men of Jabesh said to him, “Make a treaty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7447C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7447C\"></sup> with us, and we will be subject to you.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But Nahash the Ammonite replied, “I will make a treaty with you only on the condition<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7448D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7448D\"></sup> that I gouge<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7448E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7448E\"></sup> out the right eye of every one of you and so bring disgrace<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7448F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7448F\"></sup> on all Israel.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The elders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7449G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7449G\"></sup> of Jabesh said to him, “Give us seven days so we can send messengers throughout Israel; if no one comes to rescue<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7449H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7449H\"></sup> us, we will surrender<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7449I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7449I\"></sup> to you.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When the messengers came to Gibeah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7450J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7450J\"></sup> of Saul and reported these terms to the people, they all wept<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7450K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7450K\"></sup> aloud.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Just then Saul was returning from the fields, behind his oxen, and he asked, “What is wrong with everyone? Why are they weeping?” Then they repeated to him what the men of Jabesh had said.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When Saul heard their words, the Spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7452L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7452L\"></sup> of God came powerfully upon him, and he burned with anger.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He took a pair of oxen,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7453M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7453M\"></sup> cut them into pieces, and sent the pieces by messengers throughout Israel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7453N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7453N\"></sup> proclaiming, “This is what will be done to the oxen of anyone<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7453O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7453O\"></sup> who does not follow Saul and Samuel.” Then the terror of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> fell on the people, and they came out together as one.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7453P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7453P\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When Saul mustered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7454Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7454Q\"></sup> them at Bezek,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7454R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7454R\"></sup> the men of Israel numbered three hundred thousand and those of Judah thirty thousand.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>They told the messengers who had come, “Say to the men of Jabesh Gilead, ‘By the time the sun is hot tomorrow, you will be rescued.’” When the messengers went and reported this to the men of Jabesh, they were elated.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>They said to the Ammonites, “Tomorrow we will surrender<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7456S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7456S\"></sup> to you, and you can do to us whatever you like.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The next day Saul separated his men into three divisions;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7457T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7457T\"></sup> during the last watch of the night they broke into the camp of the Ammonites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7457U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7457U\"></sup> and slaughtered them until the heat of the day. Those who survived were scattered, so that no two of them were left together.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The people then said to Samuel, “Who<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7458V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7458V\"></sup> was it that asked, ‘Shall Saul reign over us?’ Turn these men over to us so that we may put them to death.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But Saul said, “No one will be put to death today,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7459W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7459W\"></sup> for this day the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has rescued<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7459X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7459X\"></sup> Israel.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then Samuel said to the people, “Come, let us go to Gilgal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7460Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7460Y\"></sup> and there renew the kingship.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7460Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7460Z\"></sup>”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So all the people went to Gilgal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7461AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7461AA\"></sup> and made Saul king<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7461AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7461AB\"></sup> in the presence of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. There they sacrificed fellowship offerings before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and Saul and all the Israelites held a great celebration."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>Samuel said to all Israel, “I have listened<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7462A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7462A\"></sup> to everything you said to me and have set a king<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7462B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7462B\"></sup> over you.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Now you have a king as your leader.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7463C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7463C\"></sup> As for me, I am old and gray, and my sons<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7463D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7463D\"></sup> are here with you. I have been your leader from my youth until this day.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Here I stand. Testify against me in the presence of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and his anointed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7464E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7464E\"></sup> Whose ox have I taken? Whose donkey<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7464F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7464F\"></sup> have I taken? Whom have I cheated? Whom have I oppressed? From whose hand have I accepted a bribe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7464G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7464G\"></sup> to make me shut my eyes? If I have done<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7464H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7464H\"></sup> any of these things, I will make it right.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7464I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7464I\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“You have not cheated or oppressed us,” they replied. “You have not taken anything from anyone’s hand.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Samuel said to them, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is witness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7466J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7466J\"></sup> against you, and also his anointed is witness this day, that you have not found anything<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7466K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7466K\"></sup> in my hand.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7466L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7466L\"></sup>”“He is witness,” they said.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Samuel said to the people, “It is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who appointed Moses and Aaron and brought<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7467M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7467M\"></sup> your ancestors up out of Egypt.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now then, stand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7468N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7468N\"></sup> here, because I am going to confront<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7468O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7468O\"></sup> you with evidence before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as to all the righteous acts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7468P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7468P\"></sup> performed by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for you and your ancestors.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“After Jacob<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7469Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7469Q\"></sup> entered Egypt, they cried<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7469R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7469R\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for help, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7469S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7469S\"></sup> Moses and Aaron, who brought your ancestors out of Egypt and settled them in this place.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“But they forgot<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7470T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7470T\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God; so he sold them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7470U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7470U\"></sup> into the hand of Sisera,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7470V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7470V\"></sup> the commander of the army of Hazor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7470W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7470W\"></sup> and into the hands of the Philistines<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7470X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7470X\"></sup> and the king of Moab,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7470Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7470Y\"></sup> who fought against them.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>They cried<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7471Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7471Z\"></sup> out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and said, ‘We have sinned; we have forsaken<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7471AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7471AA\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and served the Baals and the Ashtoreths.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7471AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7471AB\"></sup> But now deliver us from the hands of our enemies, and we will serve you.’",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent Jerub-Baal,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7472AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7472AC\"></sup> Barak,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7472AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7472AD\"></sup> Jephthah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7472AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7472AE\"></sup> and Samuel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7472AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7472AF\"></sup> and he delivered you from the hands of your enemies all around you, so that you lived in safety.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“But when you saw that Nahash<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7473AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7473AG\"></sup> king<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7473AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7473AH\"></sup> of the Ammonites was moving against you, you said to me, ‘No, we want a king to rule<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7473AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7473AI\"></sup> over us’—even though the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God was your king.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now here is the king<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7474AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7474AJ\"></sup> you have chosen, the one you asked<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7474AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7474AK\"></sup> for; see, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has set a king over you.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>If you fear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7475AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7475AL\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and serve and obey him and do not rebel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7475AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7475AM\"></sup> against his commands, and if both you and the king who reigns over you follow the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God—good!",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But if you do not obey the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and if you rebel against<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7476AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7476AN\"></sup> his commands, his hand will be against you, as it was against your ancestors.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“Now then, stand still<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7477AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7477AO\"></sup> and see<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7477AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7477AP\"></sup> this great thing the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is about to do before your eyes!",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Is it not wheat harvest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7478AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7478AQ\"></sup> now? I will call<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7478AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7478AR\"></sup> on the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to send thunder<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7478AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7478AS\"></sup> and rain.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7478AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7478AT\"></sup> And you will realize what an evil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7478AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7478AU\"></sup> thing you did in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> when you asked for a king.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Samuel called on the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7479AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7479AV\"></sup> and that same day the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent thunder and rain. So all the people stood in awe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7479AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7479AW\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and of Samuel.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The people all said to Samuel, “Pray<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7480AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7480AX\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God for your servants so that we will not die,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7480AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7480AY\"></sup> for we have added to all our other sins the evil of asking for a king.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“Do not be afraid,” Samuel replied. “You have done all this evil;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7481AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7481AZ\"></sup> yet do not turn away from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with all your heart.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Do not turn away after useless<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7482BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7482BA\"></sup> idols.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7482BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7482BB\"></sup> They can do you no good, nor can they rescue you, because they are useless.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>For the sake<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7483BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7483BC\"></sup> of his great name<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7483BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7483BD\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will not reject<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7483BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7483BE\"></sup> his people, because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was pleased to make<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7483BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7483BF\"></sup> you his own.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>As for me, far be it from me that I should sin against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by failing to pray<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7484BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7484BG\"></sup> for you. And I will teach<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7484BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7484BH\"></sup> you the way that is good and right.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But be sure to fear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7485BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7485BI\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and serve him faithfully with all your heart;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7485BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7485BJ\"></sup> consider<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7485BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7485BK\"></sup> what great<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7485BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7485BL\"></sup> things he has done for you.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Yet if you persist<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7486BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7486BM\"></sup> in doing evil, both you and your king<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7486BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7486BN\"></sup> will perish.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7486BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7486BO\"></sup>"
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>Saul was thirty years old when he became king, and he reigned over Israel forty- two years.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Saul chose three thousand men from Israel; two thousand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7488A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7488A\"></sup> were with him at Mikmash<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7488B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7488B\"></sup> and in the hill country of Bethel, and a thousand were with Jonathan at Gibeah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7488C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7488C\"></sup> in Benjamin. The rest of the men he sent back to their homes.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Jonathan attacked the Philistine outpost<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7489D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7489D\"></sup> at Geba,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7489E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7489E\"></sup> and the Philistines heard about it. Then Saul had the trumpet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7489F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7489F\"></sup> blown throughout the land and said, “Let the Hebrews hear!”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So all Israel heard the news: “Saul has attacked the Philistine outpost, and now Israel has become obnoxious<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7490G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7490G\"></sup> to the Philistines.” And the people were summoned to join Saul at Gilgal.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The Philistines assembled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7491H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7491H\"></sup> to fight Israel, with three thousand chariots, six thousand charioteers, and soldiers as numerous as the sand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7491I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7491I\"></sup> on the seashore. They went up and camped at Mikmash,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7491J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7491J\"></sup> east of Beth Aven.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7491K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7491K\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When the Israelites saw that their situation was critical and that their army was hard pressed, they hid<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7492L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7492L\"></sup> in caves and thickets, among the rocks, and in pits and cisterns.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7492M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7492M\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Some Hebrews even crossed the Jordan to the land of Gad<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7493N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7493N\"></sup> and Gilead.Saul remained at Gilgal, and all the troops with him were quaking<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7493O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7493O\"></sup> with fear.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He waited seven<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7494P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7494P\"></sup> days, the time set by Samuel; but Samuel did not come to Gilgal, and Saul’s men began to scatter.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So he said, “Bring me the burnt offering and the fellowship offerings.” And Saul offered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7495Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7495Q\"></sup> up the burnt offering.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Just as he finished making the offering, Samuel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7496R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7496R\"></sup> arrived, and Saul went out to greet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7496S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7496S\"></sup> him.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“What have you done?” asked Samuel.Saul replied, “When I saw that the men were scattering, and that you did not come at the set time, and that the Philistines were assembling at Mikmash,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7497T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7497T\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>I thought, ‘Now the Philistines will come down against me at Gilgal,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7498U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7498U\"></sup> and I have not sought the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s favor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7498V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7498V\"></sup>’ So I felt compelled to offer the burnt offering.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“You have done a foolish thing,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7499W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7499W\"></sup>” Samuel said. “You have not kept<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7499X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7499X\"></sup> the command the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God gave you; if you had, he would have established your kingdom over Israel for all time.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7499Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7499Y\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But now your kingdom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7500Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7500Z\"></sup> will not endure; the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has sought out a man after his own heart<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7500AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7500AA\"></sup> and appointed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7500AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7500AB\"></sup> him ruler<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7500AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7500AC\"></sup> of his people, because you have not kept<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7500AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7500AD\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s command.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then Samuel left Gilgal and went up to Gibeah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7501AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7501AE\"></sup> in Benjamin, and Saul counted the men who were with him. They numbered about six hundred.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7501AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7501AF\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Saul and his son Jonathan and the men with them were staying in Gibeah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7502AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7502AG\"></sup> in Benjamin, while the Philistines camped at Mikmash.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Raiding<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7503AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7503AH\"></sup> parties went out from the Philistine camp in three detachments. One turned toward Ophrah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7503AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7503AI\"></sup> in the vicinity of Shual,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>another toward Beth Horon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7504AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7504AJ\"></sup> and the third toward the borderland overlooking the Valley of Zeboyim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7504AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7504AK\"></sup> facing the wilderness.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Not a blacksmith<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7505AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7505AL\"></sup> could be found in the whole land of Israel, because the Philistines had said, “Otherwise the Hebrews will make swords or spears!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7505AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7505AM\"></sup>”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So all Israel went down to the Philistines to have their plow points, mattocks, axes and sickles sharpened.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The price was two-thirds of a shekel for sharpening plow points and mattocks, and a third of a shekel for sharpening forks and axes and for repointing goads.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So on the day of the battle not a soldier with Saul and Jonathan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7508AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7508AN\"></sup> had a sword or spear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7508AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7508AO\"></sup> in his hand; only Saul and his son Jonathan had them.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Now a detachment of Philistines had gone out to the pass<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7509AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7509AP\"></sup> at Mikmash.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7509AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7509AQ\"></sup>"
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum mid-paragraph\">14 </span><sup class=\"versenum mid-paragraph\">1 </sup>One day Jonathan son of Saul said to his young armor-bearer, “Come, let’s go over to the Philistine outpost on the other side.” But he did not tell his father.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Saul was staying<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7511A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7511A\"></sup> on the outskirts of Gibeah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7511B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7511B\"></sup> under a pomegranate tree<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7511C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7511C\"></sup> in Migron.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7511D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7511D\"></sup> With him were about six hundred men,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>among whom was Ahijah, who was wearing an ephod. He was a son of Ichabod’s<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7512E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7512E\"></sup> brother Ahitub<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7512F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7512F\"></sup> son of Phinehas, the son of Eli,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7512G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7512G\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s priest in Shiloh.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7512H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7512H\"></sup> No one was aware that Jonathan had left.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>On each side of the pass<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7513I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7513I\"></sup> that Jonathan intended to cross to reach the Philistine outpost was a cliff; one was called Bozez and the other Seneh.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>One cliff stood to the north toward Mikmash, the other to the south toward Geba.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7514J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7514J\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Jonathan said to his young armor-bearer, “Come, let’s go over to the outpost of those uncircumcised<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7515K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7515K\"></sup> men. Perhaps the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will act in our behalf. Nothing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7515L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7515L\"></sup> can hinder the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> from saving, whether by many<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7515M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7515M\"></sup> or by few.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7515N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7515N\"></sup>”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“Do all that you have in mind,” his armor-bearer said. “Go ahead; I am with you heart and soul.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Jonathan said, “Come on, then; we will cross over toward them and let them see us.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>If they say to us, ‘Wait there until we come to you,’ we will stay where we are and not go up to them.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But if they say, ‘Come up to us,’ we will climb up, because that will be our sign<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7519O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7519O\"></sup> that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given them into our hands.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7519P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7519P\"></sup>”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So both of them showed themselves to the Philistine outpost. “Look!” said the Philistines. “The Hebrews<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7520Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7520Q\"></sup> are crawling out of the holes they were hiding<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7520R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7520R\"></sup> in.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The men of the outpost shouted to Jonathan and his armor-bearer, “Come up to us and we’ll teach you a lesson.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7521S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7521S\"></sup>”So Jonathan said to his armor-bearer, “Climb up after me; the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given them into the hand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7521T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7521T\"></sup> of Israel.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Jonathan climbed up, using his hands and feet, with his armor-bearer right behind him. The Philistines fell before Jonathan, and his armor-bearer followed and killed behind him.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>In that first attack Jonathan and his armor-bearer killed some twenty men in an area of about half an acre.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then panic<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7524U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7524U\"></sup> struck the whole army—those in the camp and field, and those in the outposts and raiding<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7524V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7524V\"></sup> parties—and the ground shook. It was a panic sent by God.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Saul’s lookouts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7525W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7525W\"></sup> at Gibeah in Benjamin saw the army melting away in all directions.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Saul said to the men who were with him, “Muster the forces and see who has left us.” When they did, it was Jonathan and his armor-bearer who were not there.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Saul said to Ahijah, “Bring<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7527X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7527X\"></sup> the ark<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7527Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7527Y\"></sup> of God.” (At that time it was with the Israelites.)",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>While Saul was talking to the priest, the tumult in the Philistine camp increased more and more. So Saul said to the priest,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7528Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7528Z\"></sup> “Withdraw your hand.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Saul and all his men assembled and went to the battle. They found the Philistines in total confusion, striking<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7529AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7529AA\"></sup> each other with their swords.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Those Hebrews who had previously been with the Philistines and had gone up with them to their camp went<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7530AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7530AB\"></sup> over to the Israelites who were with Saul and Jonathan.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When all the Israelites who had hidden<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7531AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7531AC\"></sup> in the hill country of Ephraim heard that the Philistines were on the run, they joined the battle in hot pursuit.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So on that day the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> saved<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7532AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7532AD\"></sup> Israel, and the battle moved on beyond Beth Aven.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7532AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7532AE\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Now the Israelites were in distress that day, because Saul had bound the people under an oath,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7533AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7533AF\"></sup> saying, “Cursed be anyone who eats food before evening comes, before I have avenged myself on my enemies!” So none of the troops tasted food.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The entire army entered the woods, and there was honey on the ground.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>When they went into the woods, they saw the honey oozing out; yet no one put his hand to his mouth, because they feared the oath.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But Jonathan had not heard that his father had bound the people with the oath, so he reached out the end of the staff that was in his hand and dipped it into the honeycomb.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7536AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7536AG\"></sup> He raised his hand to his mouth, and his eyes brightened.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then one of the soldiers told him, “Your father bound the army under a strict oath, saying, ‘Cursed be anyone who eats food today!’ That is why the men are faint.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Jonathan said, “My father has made trouble<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7538AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7538AH\"></sup> for the country. See how my eyes brightened when I tasted a little of this honey.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>How much better it would have been if the men had eaten today some of the plunder they took from their enemies. Would not the slaughter of the Philistines have been even greater?”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>That day, after the Israelites had struck down the Philistines from Mikmash<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7540AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7540AI\"></sup> to Aijalon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7540AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7540AJ\"></sup> they were exhausted.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>They pounced on the plunder<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7541AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7541AK\"></sup> and, taking sheep, cattle and calves, they butchered them on the ground and ate them, together with the blood.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7541AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7541AL\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Then someone said to Saul, “Look, the men are sinning against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by eating meat that has blood<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7542AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7542AM\"></sup> in it.”“You have broken faith,” he said. “Roll a large stone over here at once.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then he said, “Go out among the men and tell them, ‘Each of you bring me your cattle and sheep, and slaughter them here and eat them. Do not sin against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by eating meat with blood still<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7543AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7543AN\"></sup> in it.’”So everyone brought his ox that night and slaughtered it there.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Then Saul built an altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7544AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7544AO\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; it was the first time he had done this.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Saul said, “Let us go down and pursue the Philistines by night and plunder them till dawn, and let us not leave one of them alive.”“Do whatever seems best to you,” they replied.But the priest said, “Let us inquire<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7545AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7545AP\"></sup> of God here.”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>So Saul asked God, “Shall I go down and pursue the Philistines? Will you give them into Israel’s hand?” But God did not answer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7546AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7546AQ\"></sup> him that day.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Saul therefore said, “Come here, all you who are leaders of the army, and let us find out what sin has been committed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7547AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7547AR\"></sup> today.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>As surely as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who rescues Israel lives,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7548AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7548AS\"></sup> even if the guilt lies with my son Jonathan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7548AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7548AT\"></sup> he must die.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7548AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7548AU\"></sup> But not one of them said a word.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Saul then said to all the Israelites, “You stand over there; I and Jonathan my son will stand over here.”“Do what seems best to you,” they replied.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Then Saul prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, “Why have you not answered your servant today? If the fault is in me or my son Jonathan, respond with Urim, but if the men of Israel are at fault, respond with Thummim.” Jonathan and Saul were taken by lot, and the men were cleared.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Saul said, “Cast the lot<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7551AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7551AV\"></sup> between me and Jonathan my son.” And Jonathan was taken.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Then Saul said to Jonathan, “Tell me what you have done.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7552AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7552AW\"></sup>So Jonathan told him, “I tasted a little honey<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7552AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7552AX\"></sup> with the end of my staff. And now I must die!”",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Saul said, “May God deal with me, be it ever so severely,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7553AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7553AY\"></sup> if you do not die, Jonathan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7553AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7553AZ\"></sup>”",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>But the men said to Saul, “Should Jonathan die—he who has brought about this great deliverance in Israel? Never! As surely as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, not a hair<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7554BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7554BA\"></sup> of his head will fall to the ground, for he did this today with God’s help.” So the men rescued<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7554BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7554BB\"></sup> Jonathan, and he was not put to death.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Then Saul stopped pursuing the Philistines, and they withdrew to their own land.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>After Saul had assumed rule over Israel, he fought against their enemies on every side: Moab,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7556BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7556BC\"></sup> the Ammonites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7556BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7556BD\"></sup> Edom,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7556BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7556BE\"></sup> the kings of Zobah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7556BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7556BF\"></sup> and the Philistines. Wherever he turned, he inflicted punishment on them.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>He fought valiantly and defeated the Amalekites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7557BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7557BG\"></sup> delivering Israel from the hands of those who had plundered them.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>Saul’s sons were Jonathan, Ishvi and Malki-Shua.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7558BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7558BH\"></sup> The name of his older daughter was Merab, and that of the younger was Michal.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7558BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7558BI\"></sup>",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>His wife’s name was Ahinoam daughter of Ahimaaz. The name of the commander of Saul’s army was Abner<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7559BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7559BJ\"></sup> son of Ner, and Ner was Saul’s uncle.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7559BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7559BK\"></sup>",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Saul’s father Kish<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7560BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7560BL\"></sup> and Abner’s father Ner were sons of Abiel.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>All the days of Saul there was bitter war with the Philistines, and whenever Saul saw a mighty or brave man, he took<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7561BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7561BM\"></sup> him into his service."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>Samuel said to Saul, “I am the one the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent to anoint<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7562A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7562A\"></sup> you king over his people Israel; so listen now to the message from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> Almighty says: ‘I will punish the Amalekites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7563B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7563B\"></sup> for what they did to Israel when they waylaid them as they came up from Egypt.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now go, attack the Amalekites and totally<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7564C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7564C\"></sup> destroy all that belongs to them. Do not spare them; put to death men and women, children and infants, cattle and sheep, camels and donkeys.’”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Saul summoned the men and mustered them at Telaim—two hundred thousand foot soldiers and ten thousand from Judah.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Saul went to the city of Amalek and set an ambush in the ravine.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then he said to the Kenites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7567D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7567D\"></sup> “Go away, leave the Amalekites so that I do not destroy you along with them; for you showed kindness to all the Israelites when they came up out of Egypt.” So the Kenites moved away from the Amalekites.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then Saul attacked the Amalekites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7568E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7568E\"></sup> all the way from Havilah to Shur,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7568F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7568F\"></sup> near the eastern border of Egypt.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He took Agag<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7569G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7569G\"></sup> king of the Amalekites alive,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7569H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7569H\"></sup> and all his people he totally destroyed with the sword.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But Saul and the army spared<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7570I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7570I\"></sup> Agag and the best of the sheep and cattle, the fat calves and lambs—everything that was good. These they were unwilling to destroy completely, but everything that was despised and weak they totally destroyed.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to Samuel:",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“I regret<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7572J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7572J\"></sup> that I have made Saul king, because he has turned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7572K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7572K\"></sup> away from me and has not carried out my instructions.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7572L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7572L\"></sup> Samuel was angry,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7572M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7572M\"></sup> and he cried out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> all that night.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Early in the morning Samuel got up and went to meet Saul, but he was told, “Saul has gone to Carmel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7573N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7573N\"></sup> There he has set up a monument<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7573O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7573O\"></sup> in his own honor and has turned and gone on down to Gilgal.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When Samuel reached him, Saul said, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> bless you! I have carried out the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s instructions.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But Samuel said, “What then is this bleating of sheep in my ears? What is this lowing of cattle that I hear?”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Saul answered, “The soldiers brought them from the Amalekites; they spared the best of the sheep and cattle to sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, but we totally destroyed the rest.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“Enough!” Samuel said to Saul. “Let me tell you what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me last night.”“Tell me,” Saul replied.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Samuel said, “Although you were once small<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7578P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7578P\"></sup> in your own eyes, did you not become the head of the tribes of Israel? The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> anointed you king over Israel.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And he sent you on a mission, saying, ‘Go and completely destroy those wicked people, the Amalekites; wage war against them until you have wiped them out.’",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Why did you not obey the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>? Why did you pounce on the plunder<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7580Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7580Q\"></sup> and do evil in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“But I did obey<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7581R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7581R\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,” Saul said. “I went on the mission the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> assigned me. I completely destroyed the Amalekites and brought back Agag their king.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The soldiers took sheep and cattle from the plunder, the best of what was devoted to God, in order to sacrifice them to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God at Gilgal.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But Samuel replied:“Does the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> delight in burnt offerings and sacrificesas much as in obeying the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?To obey is better than sacrifice,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7583S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7583S\"></sup>and to heed is better than the fat of rams.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>For rebellion is like the sin of divination,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7584T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7584T\"></sup>and arrogance like the evil of idolatry.Because you have rejected<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7584U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7584U\"></sup> the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,he has rejected you as king.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then Saul said to Samuel, “I have sinned.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7585V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7585V\"></sup> I violated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7585W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7585W\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s command and your instructions. I was afraid<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7585X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7585X\"></sup> of the men and so I gave in to them.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Now I beg you, forgive<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7586Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7586Y\"></sup> my sin and come back with me, so that I may worship the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But Samuel said to him, “I will not go back with you. You have rejected<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7587Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7587Z\"></sup> the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has rejected you as king over Israel!”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>As Samuel turned to leave, Saul caught hold of the hem of his robe,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7588AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7588AA\"></sup> and it tore.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7588AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7588AB\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Samuel said to him, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has torn<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7589AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7589AC\"></sup> the kingdom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7589AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7589AD\"></sup> of Israel from you today and has given it to one of your neighbors—to one better than you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7589AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7589AE\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>He who is the Glory of Israel does not lie<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7590AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7590AF\"></sup> or change<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7590AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7590AG\"></sup> his mind; for he is not a human being, that he should change his mind.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Saul replied, “I have sinned.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7591AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7591AH\"></sup> But please honor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7591AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7591AI\"></sup> me before the elders of my people and before Israel; come back with me, so that I may worship the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>So Samuel went back with Saul, and Saul worshiped the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Then Samuel said, “Bring me Agag king of the Amalekites.”Agag came to him in chains. And he thought, “Surely the bitterness of death is past.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>But Samuel said,“As your sword has made women childless,so will your mother be childless among women.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7594AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7594AJ\"></sup>And Samuel put Agag to death before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at Gilgal.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then Samuel left for Ramah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7595AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7595AK\"></sup> but Saul went up to his home in Gibeah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7595AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7595AL\"></sup> of Saul.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Until the day Samuel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7596AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7596AM\"></sup> died, he did not go to see Saul again, though Samuel mourned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7596AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7596AN\"></sup> for him. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> regretted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7596AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7596AO\"></sup> that he had made Saul king over Israel."
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Samuel, “How long will you mourn<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7597A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7597A\"></sup> for Saul, since I have rejected<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7597B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7597B\"></sup> him as king over Israel? Fill your horn with oil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7597C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7597C\"></sup> and be on your way; I am sending you to Jesse<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7597D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7597D\"></sup> of Bethlehem. I have chosen<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7597E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7597E\"></sup> one of his sons to be king.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But Samuel said, “How can I go? If Saul hears about it, he will kill me.”The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “Take a heifer with you and say, ‘I have come to sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.’",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Invite Jesse to the sacrifice, and I will show<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7599F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7599F\"></sup> you what to do. You are to anoint<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7599G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7599G\"></sup> for me the one I indicate.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Samuel did what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said. When he arrived at Bethlehem,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7600H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7600H\"></sup> the elders of the town trembled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7600I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7600I\"></sup> when they met him. They asked, “Do you come in peace?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7600J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7600J\"></sup>”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Samuel replied, “Yes, in peace; I have come to sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Consecrate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7601K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7601K\"></sup> yourselves and come to the sacrifice with me.” Then he consecrated Jesse and his sons and invited them to the sacrifice.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When they arrived, Samuel saw Eliab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7602L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7602L\"></sup> and thought, “Surely the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s anointed stands here before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Samuel, “Do not consider his appearance or his height, for I have rejected him. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> does not look at the things people look at. People look at the outward appearance,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7603M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7603M\"></sup> but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> looks at the heart.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7603N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7603N\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Jesse called Abinadab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7604O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7604O\"></sup> and had him pass in front of Samuel. But Samuel said, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has not chosen this one either.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Jesse then had Shammah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7605P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7605P\"></sup> pass by, but Samuel said, “Nor has the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> chosen this one.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Jesse had seven of his sons pass before Samuel, but Samuel said to him, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has not chosen these.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So he asked Jesse, “Are these all<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7607Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7607Q\"></sup> the sons you have?”“There is still the youngest,” Jesse answered. “He is tending the sheep.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7607R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7607R\"></sup>Samuel said, “Send for him; we will not sit down until he arrives.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So he<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7608S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7608S\"></sup> sent for him and had him brought in. He was glowing with health and had a fine appearance and handsome<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7608T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7608T\"></sup> features.Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “Rise and anoint him; this is the one.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So Samuel took the horn of oil and anointed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7609U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7609U\"></sup> him in the presence of his brothers, and from that day on the Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7609V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7609V\"></sup> came powerfully upon David.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7609W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7609W\"></sup> Samuel then went to Ramah.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Now the Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had departed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7610X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7610X\"></sup> from Saul, and an evil spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7610Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7610Y\"></sup> from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> tormented him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7610Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7610Z\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Saul’s attendants said to him, “See, an evil spirit from God is tormenting you.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Let our lord command his servants here to search for someone who can play the lyre.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7612AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7612AA\"></sup> He will play when the evil spirit from God comes on you, and you will feel better.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So Saul said to his attendants, “Find someone who plays well and bring him to me.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>One of the servants answered, “I have seen a son of Jesse<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7614AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7614AB\"></sup> of Bethlehem who knows how to play the lyre. He is a brave man and a warrior.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7614AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7614AC\"></sup> He speaks well and is a fine-looking man. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is with<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7614AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7614AD\"></sup> him.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then Saul sent messengers to Jesse and said, “Send me your son David, who is with the sheep.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7615AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7615AE\"></sup>”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So Jesse took a donkey loaded with bread,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7616AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7616AF\"></sup> a skin of wine and a young goat and sent them with his son David to Saul.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>David came to Saul and entered his service.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7617AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7617AG\"></sup> Saul liked him very much, and David became one of his armor-bearers.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Saul sent word to Jesse, saying, “Allow David to remain in my service, for I am pleased with him.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Whenever the spirit from God came on Saul, David would take up his lyre and play. Then relief would come to Saul; he would feel better, and the evil spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7619AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7619AH\"></sup> would leave him."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>Now the Philistines gathered their forces for war and assembled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7620A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7620A\"></sup> at Sokoh in Judah. They pitched camp at Ephes Dammim, between Sokoh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7620B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7620B\"></sup> and Azekah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7620C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7620C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Saul and the Israelites assembled and camped in the Valley of Elah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7621D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7621D\"></sup> and drew up their battle line to meet the Philistines.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The Philistines occupied one hill and the Israelites another, with the valley between them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>A champion named Goliath,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7623E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7623E\"></sup> who was from Gath, came out of the Philistine camp. His height was six cubits and a span.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He had a bronze helmet on his head and wore a coat of scale armor of bronze weighing five thousand shekels;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>on his legs he wore bronze greaves, and a bronze javelin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7625F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7625F\"></sup> was slung on his back.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>His spear shaft was like a weaver’s rod,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7626G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7626G\"></sup> and its iron point weighed six hundred shekels. His shield bearer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7626H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7626H\"></sup> went ahead of him.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Goliath stood and shouted to the ranks of Israel, “Why do you come out and line up for battle? Am I not a Philistine, and are you not the servants of Saul? Choose<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7627I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7627I\"></sup> a man and have him come down to me.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>If he is able to fight and kill me, we will become your subjects; but if I overcome him and kill him, you will become our subjects and serve us.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then the Philistine said, “This day I defy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7629J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7629J\"></sup> the armies of Israel! Give me a man and let us fight each other.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7629K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7629K\"></sup>”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>On hearing the Philistine’s words, Saul and all the Israelites were dismayed and terrified.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now David was the son of an Ephrathite<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7631L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7631L\"></sup> named Jesse,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7631M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7631M\"></sup> who was from Bethlehem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7631N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7631N\"></sup> in Judah. Jesse had eight<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7631O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7631O\"></sup> sons, and in Saul’s time he was very old.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Jesse’s three oldest sons had followed Saul to the war: The firstborn was Eliab;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7632P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7632P\"></sup> the second, Abinadab;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7632Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7632Q\"></sup> and the third, Shammah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7632R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7632R\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>David was the youngest. The three oldest followed Saul,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>but David went back and forth from Saul to tend<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7634S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7634S\"></sup> his father’s sheep<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7634T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7634T\"></sup> at Bethlehem.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>For forty days the Philistine came forward every morning and evening and took his stand.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now Jesse said to his son David, “Take this ephah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7636U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7636U\"></sup> of roasted grain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7636V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7636V\"></sup> and these ten loaves of bread for your brothers and hurry to their camp.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Take along these ten cheeses to the commander of their unit. See how your brothers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7637W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7637W\"></sup> are and bring back some assurance from them.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>They are with Saul and all the men of Israel in the Valley of Elah, fighting against the Philistines.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Early in the morning David left the flock in the care of a shepherd, loaded up and set out, as Jesse had directed. He reached the camp as the army was going out to its battle positions, shouting the war cry.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Israel and the Philistines were drawing up their lines facing each other.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>David left his things with the keeper of supplies,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7641X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7641X\"></sup> ran to the battle lines and asked his brothers how they were.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>As he was talking with them, Goliath, the Philistine champion from Gath, stepped out from his lines and shouted his usual<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7642Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7642Y\"></sup> defiance, and David heard it.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Whenever the Israelites saw the man, they all fled from him in great fear.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Now the Israelites had been saying, “Do you see how this man keeps coming out? He comes out to defy Israel. The king will give great wealth to the man who kills him. He will also give him his daughter<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7644Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7644Z\"></sup> in marriage and will exempt his family from taxes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7644AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7644AA\"></sup> in Israel.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>David asked the men standing near him, “What will be done for the man who kills this Philistine and removes this disgrace<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7645AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7645AB\"></sup> from Israel? Who is this uncircumcised<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7645AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7645AC\"></sup> Philistine that he should defy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7645AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7645AD\"></sup> the armies of the living<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7645AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7645AE\"></sup> God?”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>They repeated to him what they had been saying and told him, “This is what will be done for the man who kills him.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>When Eliab, David’s oldest brother, heard him speaking with the men, he burned with anger<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7647AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7647AF\"></sup> at him and asked, “Why have you come down here? And with whom did you leave those few sheep in the wilderness? I know how conceited you are and how wicked your heart is; you came down only to watch the battle.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“Now what have I done?” said David. “Can’t I even speak?”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>He then turned away to someone else and brought up the same matter, and the men answered him as before.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>What David said was overheard and reported to Saul, and Saul sent for him.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>David said to Saul, “Let no one lose heart<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7651AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7651AG\"></sup> on account of this Philistine; your servant will go and fight him.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Saul replied,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7652AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7652AH\"></sup> “You are not able to go out against this Philistine and fight him; you are only a young man, and he has been a warrior from his youth.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>But David said to Saul, “Your servant has been keeping his father’s sheep. When a lion<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7653AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7653AI\"></sup> or a bear came and carried off a sheep from the flock,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>I went after it, struck it and rescued the sheep from its mouth. When it turned on me, I seized<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7654AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7654AJ\"></sup> it by its hair, struck it and killed it.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Your servant has killed both the lion<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7655AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7655AK\"></sup> and the bear; this uncircumcised Philistine will be like one of them, because he has defied the armies of the living God.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who rescued<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7656AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7656AL\"></sup> me from the paw of the lion<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7656AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7656AM\"></sup> and the paw of the bear will rescue me from the hand of this Philistine.”Saul said to David, “Go, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> be with<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7656AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7656AN\"></sup> you.”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Then Saul dressed David in his own<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7657AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7657AO\"></sup> tunic. He put a coat of armor on him and a bronze helmet on his head.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>David fastened on his sword over the tunic and tried walking around, because he was not used to them.“I cannot go in these,” he said to Saul, “because I am not used to them.” So he took them off.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Then he took his staff in his hand, chose five smooth stones from the stream, put them in the pouch of his shepherd’s bag and, with his sling in his hand, approached the Philistine.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Meanwhile, the Philistine, with his shield bearer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7660AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7660AP\"></sup> in front of him, kept coming closer to David.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>He looked David over and saw that he was little more than a boy, glowing with health and handsome,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7661AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7661AQ\"></sup> and he despised<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7661AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7661AR\"></sup> him.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>He said to David, “Am I a dog,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7662AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7662AS\"></sup> that you come at me with sticks?” And the Philistine cursed David by his gods.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>“Come here,” he said, “and I’ll give your flesh to the birds<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7663AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7663AT\"></sup> and the wild animals!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7663AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7663AU\"></sup>”",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>David said to the Philistine, “You come against me with sword and spear and javelin,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7664AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7664AV\"></sup> but I come against you in the name<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7664AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7664AW\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> Almighty, the God of the armies of Israel, whom you have defied.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7664AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7664AX\"></sup>",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>This day the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will deliver<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7665AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7665AY\"></sup> you into my hands, and I’ll strike you down and cut off your head. This very day I will give the carcasses<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7665AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7665AZ\"></sup> of the Philistine army to the birds and the wild animals, and the whole world<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7665BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7665BA\"></sup> will know that there is a God in Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7665BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7665BB\"></sup>",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>All those gathered here will know that it is not by sword<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7666BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7666BC\"></sup> or spear that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> saves;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7666BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7666BD\"></sup> for the battle<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7666BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7666BE\"></sup> is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s, and he will give all of you into our hands.”",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>As the Philistine moved closer to attack him, David ran quickly toward the battle line to meet him.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>Reaching into his bag and taking out a stone, he slung it and struck the Philistine on the forehead. The stone sank into his forehead, and he fell facedown on the ground.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>So David triumphed over the Philistine with a sling<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7669BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7669BF\"></sup> and a stone; without a sword in his hand he struck down the Philistine and killed him.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>David ran and stood over him. He took hold of the Philistine’s sword and drew it from the sheath. After he killed him, he cut<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7670BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7670BG\"></sup> off his head with the sword.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7670BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7670BH\"></sup>When the Philistines saw that their hero was dead, they turned and ran.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>Then the men of Israel and Judah surged forward with a shout and pursued the Philistines to the entrance of Gath and to the gates of Ekron.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7671BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7671BI\"></sup> Their dead were strewn along the Shaaraim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7671BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7671BJ\"></sup> road to Gath and Ekron.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>When the Israelites returned from chasing the Philistines, they plundered their camp.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>David took the Philistine’s head and brought it to Jerusalem; he put the Philistine’s weapons in his own tent.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>As Saul watched David<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7674BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7674BK\"></sup> going out to meet the Philistine, he said to Abner, commander of the army, “Abner,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7674BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7674BL\"></sup> whose son is that young man?”Abner replied, “As surely as you live, Your Majesty, I don’t know.”",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>The king said, “Find out whose son this young man is.”",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>As soon as David returned from killing the Philistine, Abner took him and brought him before Saul, with David still holding the Philistine’s head.",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>“Whose son are you, young man?” Saul asked him.David said, “I am the son of your servant Jesse<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7677BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7677BM\"></sup> of Bethlehem.”"
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>After David had finished talking with Saul, Jonathan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7678A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7678A\"></sup> became one in spirit with David, and he loved<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7678B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7678B\"></sup> him as himself.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7678C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7678C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>From that day Saul kept David with him and did not let him return home to his family.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And Jonathan made a covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7680D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7680D\"></sup> with David because he loved him as himself.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Jonathan took off the robe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7681E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7681E\"></sup> he was wearing and gave it to David, along with his tunic, and even his sword, his bow and his belt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7681F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7681F\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Whatever mission Saul sent him on, David was so successful<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7682G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7682G\"></sup> that Saul gave him a high rank in the army.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7682H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7682H\"></sup> This pleased all the troops, and Saul’s officers as well.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When the men were returning home after David had killed the Philistine, the women came out from all the towns of Israel to meet King Saul with singing and dancing,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7683I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7683I\"></sup> with joyful songs and with timbrels<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7683J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7683J\"></sup> and lyres.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>As they danced, they sang:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7684K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7684K\"></sup>“Saul has slain his thousands,and David his tens<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7684L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7684L\"></sup> of thousands.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Saul was very angry; this refrain displeased him greatly. “They have credited David with tens of thousands,” he thought, “but me with only thousands. What more can he get but the kingdom?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7685M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7685M\"></sup>”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And from that time on Saul kept a close<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7686N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7686N\"></sup> eye on David.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The next day an evil spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7687O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7687O\"></sup> from God came forcefully on Saul. He was prophesying in his house, while David was playing the lyre,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7687P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7687P\"></sup> as he usually<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7687Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7687Q\"></sup> did. Saul had a spear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7687R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7687R\"></sup> in his hand",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and he hurled it, saying to himself,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7688S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7688S\"></sup> “I’ll pin David to the wall.” But David eluded<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7688T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7688T\"></sup> him twice.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7688U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7688U\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Saul was afraid<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7689V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7689V\"></sup> of David, because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7689W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7689W\"></sup> was with<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7689X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7689X\"></sup> David but had departed from<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7689Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7689Y\"></sup> Saul.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So he sent David away from him and gave him command over a thousand men, and David led<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7690Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7690Z\"></sup> the troops in their campaigns.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7690AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7690AA\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>In everything he did he had great success,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7691AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7691AB\"></sup> because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7691AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7691AC\"></sup> him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When Saul saw how successful he was, he was afraid of him.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But all Israel and Judah loved David, because he led them in their campaigns.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7693AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7693AD\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Saul said to David, “Here is my older daughter<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7694AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7694AE\"></sup> Merab. I will give her to you in marriage;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7694AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7694AF\"></sup> only serve me bravely and fight the battles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7694AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7694AG\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” For Saul said to himself,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7694AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7694AH\"></sup> “I will not raise a hand against him. Let the Philistines do that!”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But David said to Saul, “Who am I,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7695AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7695AI\"></sup> and what is my family or my clan in Israel, that I should become the king’s son-in-law?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7695AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7695AJ\"></sup>”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So when the time came for Merab,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7696AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7696AK\"></sup> Saul’s daughter, to be given to David, she was given in marriage to Adriel of Meholah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7696AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7696AL\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Now Saul’s daughter Michal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7697AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7697AM\"></sup> was in love with David, and when they told Saul about it, he was pleased.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7697AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7697AN\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“I will give her to him,” he thought, “so that she may be a snare<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7698AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7698AO\"></sup> to him and so that the hand of the Philistines may be against him.” So Saul said to David, “Now you have a second opportunity to become my son-in-law.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Saul ordered his attendants: “Speak to David privately and say, ‘Look, the king likes you, and his attendants all love you; now become his son-in-law.’”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>They repeated these words to David. But David said, “Do you think it is a small matter to become the king’s son-in-law?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7700AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7700AP\"></sup> I’m only a poor man and little known.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When Saul’s servants told him what David had said,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Saul replied, “Say to David, ‘The king wants no other price<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7702AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7702AQ\"></sup> for the bride than a hundred Philistine foreskins, to take revenge<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7702AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7702AR\"></sup> on his enemies.’” Saul’s plan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7702AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7702AS\"></sup> was to have David fall by the hands of the Philistines.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>When the attendants told David these things, he was pleased to become the king’s son-in-law. So before the allotted time elapsed,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>David took his men with him and went out and killed two hundred Philistines and brought back their foreskins. They counted out the full number to the king so that David might become the king’s son-in-law. Then Saul gave him his daughter Michal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7704AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7704AT\"></sup> in marriage.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>When Saul realized that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with David and that his daughter Michal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7705AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7705AU\"></sup> loved David,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Saul became still more afraid<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7706AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7706AV\"></sup> of him, and he remained his enemy the rest of his days.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The Philistine commanders continued to go out to battle, and as often as they did, David met with more success<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7707AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7707AW\"></sup> than the rest of Saul’s officers, and his name became well known."
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>Saul told his son Jonathan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7708A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7708A\"></sup> and all the attendants to kill<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7708B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7708B\"></sup> David. But Jonathan had taken a great liking to David",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and warned him, “My father Saul is looking for a chance to kill you. Be on your guard tomorrow morning; go into hiding<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7709C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7709C\"></sup> and stay there.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>I will go out and stand with my father in the field where you are. I’ll speak<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7710D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7710D\"></sup> to him about you and will tell you what I find out.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Jonathan spoke<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7711E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7711E\"></sup> well of David to Saul his father and said to him, “Let not the king do wrong<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7711F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7711F\"></sup> to his servant David; he has not wronged you, and what he has done has benefited you greatly.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He took his life<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7712G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7712G\"></sup> in his hands when he killed the Philistine. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> won a great victory<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7712H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7712H\"></sup> for all Israel, and you saw it and were glad. Why then would you do wrong to an innocent<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7712I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7712I\"></sup> man like David by killing him for no reason?”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Saul listened to Jonathan and took this oath: “As surely as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, David will not be put to death.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So Jonathan called David and told him the whole conversation. He brought him to Saul, and David was with Saul as before.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7714J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7714J\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Once more war broke out, and David went out and fought the Philistines. He struck them with such force that they fled before him.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But an evil spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7716K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7716K\"></sup> from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came on Saul as he was sitting in his house with his spear in his hand. While David was playing the lyre,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7716L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7716L\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Saul tried to pin him to the wall with his spear, but David eluded<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7717M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7717M\"></sup> him as Saul drove the spear into the wall. That night David made good his escape.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Saul sent men to David’s house to watch<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7718N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7718N\"></sup> it and to kill him in the morning.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7718O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7718O\"></sup> But Michal, David’s wife, warned him, “If you don’t run for your life tonight, tomorrow you’ll be killed.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So Michal let David down through a window,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7719P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7719P\"></sup> and he fled and escaped.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then Michal took an idol<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7720Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7720Q\"></sup> and laid it on the bed, covering it with a garment and putting some goats’ hair at the head.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When Saul sent the men to capture David, Michal said,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7721R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7721R\"></sup> “He is ill.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then Saul sent the men back to see David and told them, “Bring him up to me in his bed so that I may kill him.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But when the men entered, there was the idol in the bed, and at the head was some goats’ hair.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Saul said to Michal, “Why did you deceive me like this and send my enemy away so that he escaped?”Michal told him, “He said to me, ‘Let me get away. Why should I kill you?’”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When David had fled and made his escape, he went to Samuel at Ramah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7725S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7725S\"></sup> and told him all that Saul had done to him. Then he and Samuel went to Naioth and stayed there.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Word came to Saul: “David is in Naioth at Ramah”;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>so he sent men to capture him. But when they saw a group of prophets<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7727T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7727T\"></sup> prophesying, with Samuel standing there as their leader, the Spirit of God came on<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7727U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7727U\"></sup> Saul’s men, and they also prophesied.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7727V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7727V\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Saul was told about it, and he sent more men, and they prophesied too. Saul sent men a third time, and they also prophesied.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Finally, he himself left for Ramah and went to the great cistern at Seku. And he asked, “Where are Samuel and David?”“Over in Naioth at Ramah,” they said.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So Saul went to Naioth at Ramah. But the Spirit of God came even on him, and he walked along prophesying<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7730W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7730W\"></sup> until he came to Naioth.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>He stripped<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7731X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7731X\"></sup> off his garments, and he too prophesied in Samuel’s<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7731Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7731Y\"></sup> presence. He lay naked all that day and all that night. This is why people say, “Is Saul also among the prophets?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7731Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7731Z\"></sup>"
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>Then David fled from Naioth at Ramah and went to Jonathan and asked, “What have I done? What is my crime? How have I wronged<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7732A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7732A\"></sup> your father, that he is trying to kill me?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7732B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7732B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Never!” Jonathan replied. “You are not going to die! Look, my father doesn’t do anything, great or small, without letting me know. Why would he hide this from me? It isn’t so!”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But David took an oath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7734C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7734C\"></sup> and said, “Your father knows very well that I have found favor in your eyes, and he has said to himself, ‘Jonathan must not know this or he will be grieved.’ Yet as surely as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives and as you live, there is only a step between me and death.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Jonathan said to David, “Whatever you want me to do, I’ll do for you.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So David said, “Look, tomorrow is the New Moon feast,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7736D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7736D\"></sup> and I am supposed to dine with the king; but let me go and hide<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7736E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7736E\"></sup> in the field until the evening of the day after tomorrow.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>If your father misses me at all, tell him, ‘David earnestly asked my permission<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7737F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7737F\"></sup> to hurry to Bethlehem,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7737G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7737G\"></sup> his hometown, because an annual<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7737H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7737H\"></sup> sacrifice is being made there for his whole clan.’",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>If he says, ‘Very well,’ then your servant is safe. But if he loses his temper,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7738I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7738I\"></sup> you can be sure that he is determined<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7738J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7738J\"></sup> to harm me.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>As for you, show kindness to your servant, for you have brought him into a covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7739K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7739K\"></sup> with you before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. If I am guilty, then kill<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7739L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7739L\"></sup> me yourself! Why hand me over to your father?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“Never!” Jonathan said. “If I had the least inkling that my father was determined to harm you, wouldn’t I tell you?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>David asked, “Who will tell me if your father answers you harshly?”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“Come,” Jonathan said, “let’s go out into the field.” So they went there together.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Jonathan said to David, “I swear by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, that I will surely sound<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7743M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7743M\"></sup> out my father by this time the day after tomorrow! If he is favorably disposed toward you, will I not send you word and let you know?",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But if my father intends to harm you, may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> deal with Jonathan, be it ever so severely,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7744N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7744N\"></sup> if I do not let you know and send you away in peace. May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> be with<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7744O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7744O\"></sup> you as he has been with my father.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But show me unfailing kindness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7745P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7745P\"></sup> like the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s kindness as long as I live, so that I may not be killed,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and do not ever cut off your kindness from my family<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7746Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7746Q\"></sup>—not even when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has cut off every one of David’s enemies from the face of the earth.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So Jonathan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7747R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7747R\"></sup> made a covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7747S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7747S\"></sup> with the house of David, saying, “May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> call David’s enemies to account.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7747T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7747T\"></sup>”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And Jonathan had David reaffirm his oath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7748U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7748U\"></sup> out of love for him, because he loved him as he loved himself.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Jonathan said to David, “Tomorrow is the New Moon feast. You will be missed, because your seat will be empty.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7749V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7749V\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The day after tomorrow, toward evening, go to the place where you hid<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7750W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7750W\"></sup> when this trouble began, and wait by the stone Ezel.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>I will shoot three arrows<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7751X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7751X\"></sup> to the side of it, as though I were shooting at a target.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then I will send a boy and say, ‘Go, find the arrows.’ If I say to him, ‘Look, the arrows are on this side of you; bring them here,’ then come, because, as surely as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, you are safe; there is no danger.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But if I say to the boy, ‘Look, the arrows are beyond<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7753Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7753Y\"></sup> you,’ then you must go, because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has sent you away.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And about the matter you and I discussed—remember, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is witness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7754Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7754Z\"></sup> between you and me forever.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So David hid in the field, and when the New Moon feast<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7755AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7755AA\"></sup> came, the king sat down to eat.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He sat in his customary place by the wall, opposite Jonathan, and Abner sat next to Saul, but David’s place was empty.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7756AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7756AB\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Saul said nothing that day, for he thought, “Something must have happened to David to make him ceremonially unclean—surely he is unclean.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7757AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7757AC\"></sup>”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But the next day, the second day of the month, David’s place was empty again. Then Saul said to his son Jonathan, “Why hasn’t the son of Jesse come to the meal, either yesterday or today?”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Jonathan answered, “David earnestly asked me for permission<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7759AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7759AD\"></sup> to go to Bethlehem.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>He said, ‘Let me go, because our family is observing a sacrifice<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7760AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7760AE\"></sup> in the town and my brother has ordered me to be there. If I have found favor in your eyes, let me get away to see my brothers.’ That is why he has not come to the king’s table.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Saul’s anger flared up at Jonathan and he said to him, “You son of a perverse and rebellious woman! Don’t I know that you have sided with the son of Jesse to your own shame and to the shame of the mother who bore you?",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>As long as the son of Jesse lives on this earth, neither you nor your kingdom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7762AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7762AF\"></sup> will be established. Now send someone to bring him to me, for he must die!”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“Why<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7763AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7763AG\"></sup> should he be put to death? What<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7763AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7763AH\"></sup> has he done?” Jonathan asked his father.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>But Saul hurled his spear at him to kill him. Then Jonathan knew that his father intended<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7764AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7764AI\"></sup> to kill David.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Jonathan got up from the table in fierce anger; on that second day of the feast he did not eat, because he was grieved at his father’s shameful treatment of David.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>In the morning Jonathan went out to the field for his meeting with David. He had a small boy with him,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>and he said to the boy, “Run and find the arrows I shoot.” As the boy ran, he shot an arrow beyond him.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>When the boy came to the place where Jonathan’s arrow had fallen, Jonathan called out after him, “Isn’t the arrow beyond<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7768AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7768AJ\"></sup> you?”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Then he shouted, “Hurry! Go quickly! Don’t stop!” The boy picked up the arrow and returned to his master.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>(The boy knew nothing about all this; only Jonathan and David knew.)",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Then Jonathan gave his weapons to the boy and said, “Go, carry them back to town.”",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>After the boy had gone, David got up from the south side of the stone and bowed down before Jonathan three times, with his face to the ground.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7772AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7772AK\"></sup> Then they kissed each other and wept together—but David wept the most.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Jonathan said to David, “Go in peace,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7773AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7773AL\"></sup> for we have sworn friendship<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7773AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7773AM\"></sup> with each other in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7773AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7773AN\"></sup> saying, ‘The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is witness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7773AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7773AO\"></sup> between you and me, and between your descendants and my descendants forever.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7773AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7773AP\"></sup>’” Then David left, and Jonathan went back to the town."
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span>David went to Nob,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7774A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7774A\"></sup> to Ahimelek the priest. Ahimelek trembled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7774B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7774B\"></sup> when he met him, and asked, “Why are you alone? Why is no one with you?”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>David answered Ahimelek the priest, “The king sent me on a mission and said to me, ‘No one is to know anything about the mission I am sending you on.’ As for my men, I have told them to meet me at a certain place.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now then, what do you have on hand? Give me five loaves of bread, or whatever you can find.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But the priest answered David, “I don’t have any ordinary bread<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7777C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7777C\"></sup> on hand; however, there is some consecrated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7777D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7777D\"></sup> bread here—provided the men have kept<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7777E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7777E\"></sup> themselves from women.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>David replied, “Indeed women have been kept from us, as usual<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7778F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7778F\"></sup> whenever I set out. The men’s bodies are holy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7778G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7778G\"></sup> even on missions that are not holy. How much more so today!”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So the priest gave him the consecrated bread,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7779H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7779H\"></sup> since there was no bread there except the bread of the Presence that had been removed from before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and replaced by hot bread on the day it was taken away.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now one of Saul’s servants was there that day, detained before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; he was Doeg<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7780I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7780I\"></sup> the Edomite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7780J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7780J\"></sup> Saul’s chief shepherd.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>David asked Ahimelek, “Don’t you have a spear or a sword here? I haven’t brought my sword or any other weapon, because the king’s mission was urgent.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The priest replied, “The sword<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7782K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7782K\"></sup> of Goliath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7782L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7782L\"></sup> the Philistine, whom you killed in the Valley of Elah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7782M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7782M\"></sup> is here; it is wrapped in a cloth behind the ephod. If you want it, take it; there is no sword here but that one.”David said, “There is none like it; give it to me.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>That day David fled from Saul and went<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7783N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7783N\"></sup> to Achish king of Gath.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But the servants of Achish said to him, “Isn’t this David, the king of the land? Isn’t he the one they sing about in their dances:“‘Saul has slain his thousands,and David his tens of thousands’?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7784O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7784O\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>David took these words to heart and was very much afraid of Achish king of Gath.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So he pretended to be insane<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7786P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7786P\"></sup> in their presence; and while he was in their hands he acted like a madman, making marks on the doors of the gate and letting saliva run down his beard.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Achish said to his servants, “Look at the man! He is insane! Why bring him to me?",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Am I so short of madmen that you have to bring this fellow here to carry on like this in front of me? Must this man come into my house?”"
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span>David left Gath and escaped to the cave<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7789A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7789A\"></sup> of Adullam.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7789B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7789B\"></sup> When his brothers and his father’s household heard about it, they went down to him there.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>All those who were in distress or in debt or discontented gathered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7790C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7790C\"></sup> around him, and he became their commander. About four hundred men were with him.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>From there David went to Mizpah in Moab and said to the king of Moab, “Would you let my father and mother come and stay with you until I learn what God will do for me?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So he left them with the king of Moab,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7792D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7792D\"></sup> and they stayed with him as long as David was in the stronghold.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But the prophet Gad<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7793E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7793E\"></sup> said to David, “Do not stay in the stronghold. Go into the land of Judah.” So David left and went to the forest of Hereth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7793F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7793F\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Now Saul heard that David and his men had been discovered. And Saul was seated,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7794G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7794G\"></sup> spear in hand, under the tamarisk<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7794H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7794H\"></sup> tree on the hill at Gibeah, with all his officials standing at his side.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He said to them, “Listen, men of Benjamin! Will the son of Jesse give all of you fields and vineyards? Will he make all of you commanders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7795I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7795I\"></sup> of thousands and commanders of hundreds?",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Is that why you have all conspired<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7796J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7796J\"></sup> against me? No one tells me when my son makes a covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7796K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7796K\"></sup> with the son of Jesse.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7796L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7796L\"></sup> None of you is concerned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7796M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7796M\"></sup> about me or tells me that my son has incited my servant to lie in wait for me, as he does today.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But Doeg<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7797N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7797N\"></sup> the Edomite, who was standing with Saul’s officials, said, “I saw the son of Jesse come to Ahimelek son of Ahitub<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7797O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7797O\"></sup> at Nob.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7797P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7797P\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Ahimelek inquired<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7798Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7798Q\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for him; he also gave him provisions<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7798R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7798R\"></sup> and the sword<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7798S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7798S\"></sup> of Goliath the Philistine.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then the king sent for the priest Ahimelek son of Ahitub and all the men of his family, who were the priests at Nob, and they all came to the king.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Saul said, “Listen now, son of Ahitub.”“Yes, my lord,” he answered.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Saul said to him, “Why have you conspired<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7801T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7801T\"></sup> against me, you and the son of Jesse, giving him bread and a sword and inquiring of God for him, so that he has rebelled against me and lies in wait for me, as he does today?”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Ahimelek answered the king, “Who<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7802U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7802U\"></sup> of all your servants is as loyal as David, the king’s son-in-law, captain of your bodyguard and highly respected in your household?",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Was that day the first time I inquired of God for him? Of course not! Let not the king accuse your servant or any of his father’s family, for your servant knows nothing at all about this whole affair.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But the king said, “You will surely die, Ahimelek, you and your whole family.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7804V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7804V\"></sup>”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then the king ordered the guards at his side: “Turn and kill the priests of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, because they too have sided with David. They knew he was fleeing, yet they did not tell me.”But the king’s officials were unwilling<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7805W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7805W\"></sup> to raise a hand to strike the priests of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The king then ordered Doeg, “You turn and strike down the priests.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7806X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7806X\"></sup> So Doeg the Edomite turned and struck them down. That day he killed eighty-five men who wore the linen ephod.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7806Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7806Y\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He also put to the sword<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7807Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7807Z\"></sup> Nob,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7807AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7807AA\"></sup> the town of the priests, with its men and women, its children and infants, and its cattle, donkeys and sheep.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But one son of Ahimelek son of Ahitub,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7808AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7808AB\"></sup> named Abiathar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7808AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7808AC\"></sup> escaped and fled to join David.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7808AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7808AD\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He told David that Saul had killed the priests of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then David said to Abiathar, “That day, when Doeg<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7810AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7810AE\"></sup> the Edomite was there, I knew he would be sure to tell Saul. I am responsible for the death of your whole family.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Stay with me; don’t be afraid. The man who wants to kill you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7811AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7811AF\"></sup> is trying to kill me too. You will be safe with me.”"
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span>When David was told, “Look, the Philistines are fighting against Keilah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7812A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7812A\"></sup> and are looting the threshing floors,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7812B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7812B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>he inquired<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7813C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7813C\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying, “Shall I go and attack these Philistines?”The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> answered him, “Go, attack the Philistines and save Keilah.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But David’s men said to him, “Here in Judah we are afraid. How much more, then, if we go to Keilah against the Philistine forces!”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Once again David inquired<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7815D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7815D\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> answered him, “Go down to Keilah, for I am going to give the Philistines<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7815E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7815E\"></sup> into your hand.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7815F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7815F\"></sup>”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So David and his men went to Keilah, fought the Philistines and carried off their livestock. He inflicted heavy losses on the Philistines and saved the people of Keilah.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>(Now Abiathar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7817G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7817G\"></sup> son of Ahimelek had brought the ephod<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7817H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7817H\"></sup> down with him when he fled to David at Keilah.)",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Saul was told that David had gone to Keilah, and he said, “God has delivered him into my hands,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7818I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7818I\"></sup> for David has imprisoned himself by entering a town with gates and bars.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7818J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7818J\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And Saul called up all his forces for battle, to go down to Keilah to besiege David and his men.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When David learned that Saul was plotting against him, he said to Abiathar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7820K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7820K\"></sup> the priest, “Bring the ephod.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7820L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7820L\"></sup>”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>David said, “<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, God of Israel, your servant has heard definitely that Saul plans to come to Keilah and destroy the town on account of me.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Will the citizens of Keilah surrender me to him? Will Saul come down, as your servant has heard? <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, God of Israel, tell your servant.”And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “He will.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Again David asked, “Will the citizens of Keilah surrender<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7823M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7823M\"></sup> me and my men to Saul?”And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “They will.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So David and his men,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7824N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7824N\"></sup> about six hundred in number, left Keilah and kept moving from place to place. When Saul was told that David had escaped from Keilah, he did not go there.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>David stayed in the wilderness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7825O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7825O\"></sup> strongholds and in the hills of the Desert of Ziph.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7825P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7825P\"></sup> Day after day Saul searched<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7825Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7825Q\"></sup> for him, but God did not<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7825R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7825R\"></sup> give David into his hands.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>While David was at Horesh in the Desert of Ziph, he learned that Saul had come out to take his life.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7826S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7826S\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And Saul’s son Jonathan went to David at Horesh and helped him find strength<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7827T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7827T\"></sup> in God.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“Don’t be afraid,” he said. “My father Saul will not lay a hand on you. You will be king<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7828U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7828U\"></sup> over Israel, and I will be second to you. Even my father Saul knows this.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The two of them made a covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7829V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7829V\"></sup> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Then Jonathan went home, but David remained at Horesh.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The Ziphites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7830W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7830W\"></sup> went up to Saul at Gibeah and said, “Is not David hiding among us<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7830X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7830X\"></sup> in the strongholds at Horesh, on the hill of Hakilah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7830Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7830Y\"></sup> south of Jeshimon?",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Now, Your Majesty, come down whenever it pleases you to do so, and we will be responsible for giving<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7831Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7831Z\"></sup> him into your hands.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Saul replied, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> bless<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7832AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7832AA\"></sup> you for your concern<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7832AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7832AB\"></sup> for me.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Go and get more information. Find out where David usually goes and who has seen him there. They tell me he is very crafty.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Find out about all the hiding places he uses and come back to me with definite information. Then I will go with you; if he is in the area, I will track<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7834AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7834AC\"></sup> him down among all the clans of Judah.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So they set out and went to Ziph ahead of Saul. Now David and his men were in the Desert of Maon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7835AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7835AD\"></sup> in the Arabah south of Jeshimon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7835AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7835AE\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Saul and his men began the search, and when David was told about it, he went down to the rock and stayed in the Desert of Maon. When Saul heard this, he went into the Desert of Maon in pursuit of David.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Saul<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7837AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7837AF\"></sup> was going along one side of the mountain, and David and his men were on the other side, hurrying to get away from Saul. As Saul and his forces were closing in on David and his men to capture them,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>a messenger came to Saul, saying, “Come quickly! The Philistines are raiding the land.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then Saul broke off his pursuit of David and went to meet the Philistines. That is why they call this place Sela Hammahlekoth.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And David went up from there and lived in the strongholds<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7840AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7840AG\"></sup> of En Gedi.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7840AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7840AH\"></sup>"
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span>After Saul returned from pursuing the Philistines, he was told, “David is in the Desert of En Gedi.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7841A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7841A\"></sup>”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So Saul took three thousand able young men from all Israel and set out to look<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7842B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7842B\"></sup> for David and his men near the Crags of the Wild Goats.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He came to the sheep pens along the way; a cave<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7843C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7843C\"></sup> was there, and Saul went in to relieve<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7843D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7843D\"></sup> himself. David and his men were far back in the cave.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The men said, “This is the day the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7844E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7844E\"></sup> of when he said to you, ‘I will give your enemy into your hands for you to deal with as you wish.’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7844F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7844F\"></sup> Then David crept up unnoticed and cut<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7844G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7844G\"></sup> off a corner of Saul’s robe.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Afterward, David was conscience-stricken<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7845H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7845H\"></sup> for having cut off a corner of his robe.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He said to his men, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> forbid that I should do such a thing to my master, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s anointed,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7846I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7846I\"></sup> or lay my hand on him; for he is the anointed of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>With these words David sharply rebuked his men and did not allow them to attack Saul. And Saul left the cave and went his way.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then David went out of the cave and called out to Saul, “My lord the king!” When Saul looked behind him, David bowed down and prostrated himself with his face to the ground.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7848J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7848J\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He said to Saul, “Why do you listen<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7849K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7849K\"></sup> when men say, ‘David is bent on harming<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7849L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7849L\"></sup> you’?",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>This day you have seen with your own eyes how the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> delivered you into my hands in the cave. Some urged me to kill you, but I spared<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7850M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7850M\"></sup> you; I said, ‘I will not lay my hand on my lord, because he is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s anointed.’",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>See, my father, look at this piece of your robe in my hand! I cut<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7851N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7851N\"></sup> off the corner of your robe but did not kill you. See that there is nothing in my hand to indicate that I am guilty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7851O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7851O\"></sup> of wrongdoing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7851P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7851P\"></sup> or rebellion. I have not wronged<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7851Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7851Q\"></sup> you, but you are hunting<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7851R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7851R\"></sup> me down to take my life.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7851S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7851S\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> judge<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7852T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7852T\"></sup> between you and me. And may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> avenge<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7852U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7852U\"></sup> the wrongs you have done to me, but my hand will not touch you.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>As the old saying goes, ‘From evildoers come evil deeds,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7853V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7853V\"></sup>’ so my hand will not touch you.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“Against whom has the king of Israel come out? Who are you pursuing? A dead dog?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7854W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7854W\"></sup> A flea?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7854X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7854X\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> be our judge<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7855Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7855Y\"></sup> and decide<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7855Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7855Z\"></sup> between us. May he consider my cause and uphold<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7855AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7855AA\"></sup> it; may he vindicate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7855AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7855AB\"></sup> me by delivering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7855AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7855AC\"></sup> me from your hand.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When David finished saying this, Saul asked, “Is that your voice,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7856AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7856AD\"></sup> David my son?” And he wept aloud.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“You are more righteous than I,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7857AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7857AE\"></sup> he said. “You have treated me well,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7857AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7857AF\"></sup> but I have treated you badly.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7857AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7857AG\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>You have just now told me about the good you did to me; the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> delivered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7858AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7858AH\"></sup> me into your hands, but you did not kill me.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>When a man finds his enemy, does he let him get away unharmed? May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> reward<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7859AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7859AI\"></sup> you well for the way you treated me today.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>I know that you will surely be king<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7860AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7860AJ\"></sup> and that the kingdom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7860AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7860AK\"></sup> of Israel will be established in your hands.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Now swear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7861AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7861AL\"></sup> to me by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that you will not kill off my descendants or wipe out my name from my father’s family.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7861AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7861AM\"></sup>”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So David gave his oath to Saul. Then Saul returned home, but David and his men went up to the stronghold.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7862AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7862AN\"></sup>"
		},
		"25": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">25 </span>Now Samuel died,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7863A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7863A\"></sup> and all Israel assembled and mourned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7863B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7863B\"></sup> for him; and they buried him at his home in Ramah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7863C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7863C\"></sup> Then David moved down into the Desert of Paran.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>A certain man in Maon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7864D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7864D\"></sup> who had property there at Carmel, was very wealthy.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7864E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7864E\"></sup> He had a thousand goats and three thousand sheep, which he was shearing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7864F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7864F\"></sup> in Carmel.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>His name was Nabal and his wife’s name was Abigail.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7865G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7865G\"></sup> She was an intelligent and beautiful woman, but her husband was surly and mean in his dealings—he was a Calebite.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7865H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7865H\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>While David was in the wilderness, he heard that Nabal was shearing sheep.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So he sent ten young men and said to them, “Go up to Nabal at Carmel and greet him in my name.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Say to him: ‘Long life to you! Good health<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7868I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7868I\"></sup> to you and your household! And good health to all that is yours!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7868J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7868J\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“‘Now I hear that it is sheep-shearing time. When your shepherds were with us, we did not mistreat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7869K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7869K\"></sup> them, and the whole time they were at Carmel nothing of theirs was missing.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Ask your own servants and they will tell you. Therefore be favorable toward my men, since we come at a festive time. Please give your servants and your son David whatever<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7870L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7870L\"></sup> you can find for them.’”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When David’s men arrived, they gave Nabal this message in David’s name. Then they waited.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Nabal answered David’s servants, “Who<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7872M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7872M\"></sup> is this David? Who is this son of Jesse? Many servants are breaking away from their masters these days.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Why should I take my bread<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7873N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7873N\"></sup> and water, and the meat I have slaughtered for my shearers, and give it to men coming from who knows where?”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>David’s men turned around and went back. When they arrived, they reported every word.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>David said to his men<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7875O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7875O\"></sup>, “Each of you strap on your sword!” So they did, and David strapped his on as well. About four hundred men went<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7875P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7875P\"></sup> up with David, while two hundred stayed with the supplies.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7875Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7875Q\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>One of the servants told Abigail, Nabal’s wife, “David sent messengers from the wilderness to give our master his greetings,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7876R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7876R\"></sup> but he hurled insults at them.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Yet these men were very good to us. They did not mistreat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7877S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7877S\"></sup> us, and the whole time we were out in the fields near them nothing was missing.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7877T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7877T\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Night and day they were a wall<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7878U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7878U\"></sup> around us the whole time we were herding our sheep near them.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now think it over and see what you can do, because disaster is hanging over our master and his whole household. He is such a wicked<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7879V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7879V\"></sup> man that no one can talk to him.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Abigail acted quickly. She took two hundred loaves of bread, two skins of wine, five dressed sheep, five seahs of roasted grain,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7880W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7880W\"></sup> a hundred cakes of raisins<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7880X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7880X\"></sup> and two hundred cakes of pressed figs, and loaded them on donkeys.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7880Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7880Y\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then she told her servants, “Go on ahead;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7881Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7881Z\"></sup> I’ll follow you.” But she did not tell<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7881AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7881AA\"></sup> her husband Nabal.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>As she came riding her donkey into a mountain ravine, there were David and his men descending toward her, and she met them.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>David had just said, “It’s been useless—all my watching over this fellow’s property in the wilderness so that nothing of his was missing.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7883AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7883AB\"></sup> He has paid<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7883AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7883AC\"></sup> me back evil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7883AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7883AD\"></sup> for good.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>May God deal with David, be it ever so severely,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7884AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7884AE\"></sup> if by morning I leave alive one male<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7884AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7884AF\"></sup> of all who belong to him!”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>When Abigail saw David, she quickly got off her donkey and bowed down before David with her face to the ground.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7885AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7885AG\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>She fell at his feet and said: “Pardon your servant, my lord,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7886AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7886AH\"></sup> and let me speak to you; hear what your servant has to say.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Please pay no attention, my lord, to that wicked man Nabal. He is just like his name—his name means Fool<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7887AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7887AI\"></sup>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7887AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7887AJ\"></sup> and folly goes with him. And as for me, your servant, I did not see the men my lord sent.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And now, my lord, as surely as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God lives and as you live, since the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has kept you from bloodshed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7888AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7888AK\"></sup> and from avenging<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7888AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7888AL\"></sup> yourself with your own hands, may your enemies and all who are intent on harming my lord be like Nabal.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7888AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7888AM\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And let this gift,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7889AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7889AN\"></sup> which your servant has brought to my lord, be given to the men who follow you.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“Please forgive<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7890AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7890AO\"></sup> your servant’s presumption. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will certainly make a lasting<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7890AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7890AP\"></sup> dynasty for my lord, because you fight the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s battles,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7890AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7890AQ\"></sup> and no wrongdoing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7890AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7890AR\"></sup> will be found in you as long as you live.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Even though someone is pursuing you to take your life,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7891AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7891AS\"></sup> the life of my lord will be bound securely in the bundle of the living by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, but the lives of your enemies he will hurl<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7891AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7891AT\"></sup> away as from the pocket of a sling.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7891AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7891AU\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>When the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has fulfilled for my lord every good thing he promised concerning him and has appointed him ruler<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7892AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7892AV\"></sup> over Israel,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>my lord will not have on his conscience the staggering burden of needless bloodshed or of having avenged himself. And when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has brought my lord success, remember<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7893AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7893AW\"></sup> your servant.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7893AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7893AX\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>David said to Abigail, “Praise<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7894AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7894AY\"></sup> be to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, who has sent you today to meet me.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>May you be blessed for your good judgment and for keeping me from bloodshed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7895AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7895AZ\"></sup> this day and from avenging myself with my own hands.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Otherwise, as surely as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, lives, who has kept me from harming you, if you had not come quickly to meet me, not one male belonging to Nabal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7896BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7896BA\"></sup> would have been left alive by daybreak.”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Then David accepted from her hand what she had brought him and said, “Go home in peace. I have heard your words and granted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7897BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7897BB\"></sup> your request.”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>When Abigail went to Nabal, he was in the house holding a banquet like that of a king. He was in high<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7898BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7898BC\"></sup> spirits and very drunk.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7898BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7898BD\"></sup> So she told<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7898BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7898BE\"></sup> him nothing at all until daybreak.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Then in the morning, when Nabal was sober, his wife told him all these things, and his heart failed him and he became like a stone.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7899BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7899BF\"></sup>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>About ten days later, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> struck<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7900BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7900BG\"></sup> Nabal and he died.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>When David heard that Nabal was dead, he said, “Praise be to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who has upheld my cause against Nabal for treating me with contempt. He has kept his servant from doing wrong and has brought Nabal’s wrongdoing down on his own head.”Then David sent word to Abigail, asking her to become his wife.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>His servants went to Carmel and said to Abigail, “David has sent us to you to take you to become his wife.”",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>She bowed down with her face to the ground and said, “I am your servant and am ready to serve you and wash the feet of my lord’s servants.”",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Abigail<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7904BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7904BH\"></sup> quickly got on a donkey and, attended by her five female servants, went with David’s messengers and became his wife.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>David had also married Ahinoam<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7905BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7905BI\"></sup> of Jezreel, and they both were his wives.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7905BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7905BJ\"></sup>",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>But Saul had given his daughter Michal, David’s wife, to Paltiel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7906BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7906BK\"></sup> son of Laish, who was from Gallim.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7906BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7906BL\"></sup>"
		},
		"26": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">26 </span>The Ziphites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7907A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7907A\"></sup> went to Saul at Gibeah and said, “Is not David hiding<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7907B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7907B\"></sup> on the hill of Hakilah, which faces Jeshimon?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7907C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7907C\"></sup>”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So Saul went down to the Desert of Ziph, with his three thousand select Israelite troops, to search<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7908D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7908D\"></sup> there for David.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Saul made his camp beside the road on the hill of Hakilah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7909E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7909E\"></sup> facing Jeshimon, but David stayed in the wilderness. When he saw that Saul had followed him there,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>he sent out scouts and learned that Saul had definitely arrived.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then David set out and went to the place where Saul had camped. He saw where Saul and Abner<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7911F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7911F\"></sup> son of Ner, the commander of the army, had lain down. Saul was lying inside the camp, with the army encamped around him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>David then asked Ahimelek the Hittite<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7912G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7912G\"></sup> and Abishai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7912H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7912H\"></sup> son of Zeruiah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7912I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7912I\"></sup> Joab’s brother, “Who will go down into the camp with me to Saul?”“I’ll go with you,” said Abishai.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So David and Abishai went to the army by night, and there was Saul, lying asleep inside the camp with his spear stuck in the ground near his head. Abner and the soldiers were lying around him.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Abishai said to David, “Today God has delivered your enemy into your hands. Now let me pin him to the ground with one thrust of the spear; I won’t strike him twice.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But David said to Abishai, “Don’t destroy him! Who can lay a hand on the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s anointed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7915J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7915J\"></sup> and be guiltless?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7915K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7915K\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>As surely as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives,” he said, “the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> himself will strike<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7916L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7916L\"></sup> him, or his time<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7916M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7916M\"></sup> will come and he will die,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7916N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7916N\"></sup> or he will go into battle and perish.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> forbid that I should lay a hand on the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s anointed. Now get the spear and water jug that are near his head, and let’s go.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So David took the spear and water jug near Saul’s head, and they left. No one saw or knew about it, nor did anyone wake up. They were all sleeping, because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had put them into a deep sleep.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7918O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7918O\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then David crossed over to the other side and stood on top of the hill some distance away; there was a wide space between them.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He called out to the army and to Abner son of Ner, “Aren’t you going to answer me, Abner?”Abner replied, “Who are you who calls to the king?”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>David said, “You’re a man, aren’t you? And who is like you in Israel? Why didn’t you guard your lord the king? Someone came to destroy your lord the king.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>What you have done is not good. As surely as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, you and your men must die, because you did not guard your master, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s anointed. Look around you. Where are the king’s spear and water jug that were near his head?”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Saul recognized David’s voice and said, “Is that your voice,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7923P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7923P\"></sup> David my son?”David replied, “Yes it is, my lord the king.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And he added, “Why is my lord pursuing his servant? What have I done, and what wrong<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7924Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7924Q\"></sup> am I guilty of?",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now let my lord the king listen<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7925R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7925R\"></sup> to his servant’s words. If the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has incited you against me, then may he accept an offering.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7925S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7925S\"></sup> If, however, people have done it, may they be cursed before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>! They have driven me today from my share in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s inheritance<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7925T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7925T\"></sup> and have said, ‘Go, serve other gods.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7925U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7925U\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Now do not let my blood<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7926V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7926V\"></sup> fall to the ground far from the presence of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. The king of Israel has come out to look for a flea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7926W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7926W\"></sup>—as one hunts a partridge in the mountains.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7926X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7926X\"></sup>”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Saul said, “I have sinned.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7927Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7927Y\"></sup> Come back, David my son. Because you considered my life precious<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7927Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7927Z\"></sup> today, I will not try to harm you again. Surely I have acted like a fool and have been terribly wrong.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“Here is the king’s spear,” David answered. “Let one of your young men come over and get it.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> rewards<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7929AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7929AA\"></sup> everyone for their righteousness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7929AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7929AB\"></sup> and faithfulness. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> delivered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7929AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7929AC\"></sup> you into my hands today, but I would not lay a hand on the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s anointed.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>As surely as I valued your life today, so may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> value my life and deliver<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7930AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7930AD\"></sup> me from all trouble.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then Saul said to David, “May you be blessed,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7931AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7931AE\"></sup> David my son; you will do great things and surely triumph.”So David went on his way, and Saul returned home."
		},
		"27": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">27 </span>But David thought to himself, “One of these days I will be destroyed by the hand of Saul. The best thing I can do is to escape to the land of the Philistines. Then Saul will give up searching for me anywhere in Israel, and I will slip out of his hand.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So David and the six hundred men<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7933A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7933A\"></sup> with him left and went<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7933B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7933B\"></sup> over to Achish<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7933C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7933C\"></sup> son of Maok king of Gath.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>David and his men settled in Gath with Achish. Each man had his family with him, and David had his two wives:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7934D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7934D\"></sup> Ahinoam of Jezreel and Abigail of Carmel, the widow of Nabal.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When Saul was told that David had fled to Gath, he no longer searched for him.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then David said to Achish, “If I have found favor in your eyes, let a place be assigned to me in one of the country towns, that I may live there. Why should your servant live in the royal city with you?”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So on that day Achish gave him Ziklag,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7937E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7937E\"></sup> and it has belonged to the kings of Judah ever since.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>David lived<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7938F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7938F\"></sup> in Philistine territory a year and four months.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now David and his men went up and raided the Geshurites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7939G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7939G\"></sup> the Girzites and the Amalekites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7939H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7939H\"></sup> (From ancient times these peoples had lived in the land extending to Shur<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7939I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7939I\"></sup> and Egypt.)",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Whenever David attacked an area, he did not leave a man or woman alive,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7940J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7940J\"></sup> but took sheep and cattle, donkeys and camels, and clothes. Then he returned to Achish.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When Achish asked, “Where did you go raiding today?” David would say, “Against the Negev of Judah” or “Against the Negev of Jerahmeel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7941K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7941K\"></sup>” or “Against the Negev of the Kenites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7941L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7941L\"></sup>”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He did not leave a man or woman alive to be brought to Gath, for he thought, “They might inform on us and say, ‘This is what David did.’” And such was his practice as long as he lived in Philistine territory.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Achish trusted David and said to himself, “He has become so obnoxious<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7943M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7943M\"></sup> to his people, the Israelites, that he will be my servant for life.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7943N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7943N\"></sup>”"
		},
		"28": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">28 </span>In those days the Philistines gathered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7944A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7944A\"></sup> their forces to fight against Israel. Achish said to David, “You must understand that you and your men will accompany me in the army.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>David said, “Then you will see for yourself what your servant can do.”Achish replied, “Very well, I will make you my bodyguard<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7945B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7945B\"></sup> for life.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now Samuel was dead,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7946C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7946C\"></sup> and all Israel had mourned for him and buried him in his own town of Ramah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7946D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7946D\"></sup> Saul had expelled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7946E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7946E\"></sup> the mediums and spiritists<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7946F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7946F\"></sup> from the land.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The Philistines assembled and came and set up camp at Shunem,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7947G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7947G\"></sup> while Saul gathered all Israel and set up camp at Gilboa.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7947H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7947H\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When Saul saw the Philistine army, he was afraid; terror<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7948I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7948I\"></sup> filled his heart.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He inquired<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7949J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7949J\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did not answer him by dreams<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7949K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7949K\"></sup> or Urim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7949L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7949L\"></sup> or prophets.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7949M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7949M\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Saul then said to his attendants, “Find me a woman who is a medium,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7950N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7950N\"></sup> so I may go and inquire of her.”“There is one in Endor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7950O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7950O\"></sup>” they said.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So Saul disguised<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7951P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7951P\"></sup> himself, putting on other clothes, and at night he and two men went to the woman. “Consult<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7951Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7951Q\"></sup> a spirit for me,” he said, “and bring up for me the one I name.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But the woman said to him, “Surely you know what Saul has done. He has cut off<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7952R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7952R\"></sup> the mediums and spiritists from the land. Why have you set a trap<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7952S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7952S\"></sup> for my life to bring about my death?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Saul swore to her by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “As surely as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, you will not be punished for this.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then the woman asked, “Whom shall I bring up for you?”“Bring up Samuel,” he said.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When the woman saw Samuel, she cried out at the top of her voice and said to Saul, “Why have you deceived me?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7955T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7955T\"></sup> You are Saul!”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The king said to her, “Don’t be afraid. What do you see?”The woman said, “I see a ghostly figure coming up out of the earth.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7956U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7956U\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“What does he look like?” he asked.“An old man wearing a robe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7957V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7957V\"></sup> is coming up,” she said.Then Saul knew it was Samuel, and he bowed down and prostrated himself with his face to the ground.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Samuel said to Saul, “Why have you disturbed me by bringing me up?”“I am in great distress,” Saul said. “The Philistines are fighting against me, and God has departed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7958W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7958W\"></sup> from me. He no longer answers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7958X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7958X\"></sup> me, either by prophets or by dreams.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7958Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7958Y\"></sup> So I have called on you to tell me what to do.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Samuel said, “Why do you consult me, now that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has departed from you and become your enemy?",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has done what he predicted through me. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has torn<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7960Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7960Z\"></sup> the kingdom out of your hands and given it to one of your neighbors—to David.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Because you did not obey<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7961AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7961AA\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> or carry out his fierce wrath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7961AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7961AB\"></sup> against the Amalekites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7961AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7961AC\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has done this to you today.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will deliver both Israel and you into the hands of the Philistines, and tomorrow you and your sons<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7962AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7962AD\"></sup> will be with me. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will also give the army of Israel into the hands of the Philistines.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Immediately Saul fell full length on the ground, filled with fear because of Samuel’s words. His strength was gone, for he had eaten nothing all that day and all that night.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When the woman came to Saul and saw that he was greatly shaken, she said, “Look, your servant has obeyed you. I took my life<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7964AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7964AE\"></sup> in my hands and did what you told me to do.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Now please listen to your servant and let me give you some food so you may eat and have the strength to go on your way.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He refused<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7966AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7966AF\"></sup> and said, “I will not eat.”But his men joined the woman in urging him, and he listened to them. He got up from the ground and sat on the couch.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The woman had a fattened calf<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7967AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7967AG\"></sup> at the house, which she butchered at once. She took some flour, kneaded it and baked bread without yeast.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then she set it before Saul and his men, and they ate. That same night they got up and left."
		},
		"29": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">29 </span>The Philistines gathered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7969A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7969A\"></sup> all their forces at Aphek,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7969B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7969B\"></sup> and Israel camped by the spring in Jezreel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7969C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7969C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>As the Philistine rulers marched with their units of hundreds and thousands, David and his men were marching at the rear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7970D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7970D\"></sup> with Achish.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The commanders of the Philistines asked, “What about these Hebrews?”Achish replied, “Is this not David,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7971E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7971E\"></sup> who was an officer of Saul king of Israel? He has already been with me for over a year,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7971F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7971F\"></sup> and from the day he left Saul until now, I have found no fault in him.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But the Philistine commanders were angry with Achish and said, “Send<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7972G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7972G\"></sup> the man back, that he may return to the place you assigned him. He must not go with us into battle, or he will turn<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7972H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7972H\"></sup> against us during the fighting. How better could he regain his master’s favor than by taking the heads of our own men?",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Isn’t this the David they sang about in their dances:“‘Saul has slain his thousands,and David his tens of thousands’?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7973I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7973I\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Achish called David and said to him, “As surely as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, you have been reliable, and I would be pleased to have you serve with me in the army. From the day<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7974J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7974J\"></sup> you came to me until today, I have found no fault in you, but the rulers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7974K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7974K\"></sup> don’t approve of you.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now turn back and go in peace; do nothing to displease the Philistine rulers.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“But what have I done?” asked David. “What have you found against your servant from the day I came to you until now? Why can’t I go and fight against the enemies of my lord the king?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Achish answered, “I know that you have been as pleasing in my eyes as an angel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7977L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7977L\"></sup> of God; nevertheless, the Philistine commanders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7977M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7977M\"></sup> have said, ‘He must not go up with us into battle.’",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now get up early, along with your master’s servants who have come with you, and leave<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7978N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7978N\"></sup> in the morning as soon as it is light.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So David and his men got up early in the morning to go back to the land of the Philistines, and the Philistines went up to Jezreel."
		},
		"30": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">30 </span>David and his men reached Ziklag<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7980A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7980A\"></sup> on the third day. Now the Amalekites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7980B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7980B\"></sup> had raided the Negev and Ziklag. They had attacked Ziklag and burned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7980C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7980C\"></sup> it,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and had taken captive the women and everyone else in it, both young and old. They killed none of them, but carried them off as they went on their way.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When David and his men reached Ziklag, they found it destroyed by fire and their wives and sons and daughters taken captive.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7982D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7982D\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So David and his men wept<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7983E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7983E\"></sup> aloud until they had no strength left to weep.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>David’s two wives<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7984F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7984F\"></sup> had been captured—Ahinoam of Jezreel and Abigail, the widow of Nabal of Carmel.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>David was greatly distressed because the men were talking of stoning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7985G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7985G\"></sup> him; each one was bitter<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7985H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7985H\"></sup> in spirit because of his sons and daughters. But David found strength<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7985I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7985I\"></sup> in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then David said to Abiathar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7986J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7986J\"></sup> the priest, the son of Ahimelek, “Bring me the ephod.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7986K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7986K\"></sup>” Abiathar brought it to him,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and David inquired<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7987L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7987L\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “Shall I pursue this raiding party? Will I overtake them?”“Pursue them,” he answered. “You will certainly overtake them and succeed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7987M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7987M\"></sup> in the rescue.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7987N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7987N\"></sup>”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>David and the six hundred men<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7988O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7988O\"></sup> with him came to the Besor Valley, where some stayed behind.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Two hundred of them were too exhausted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7989P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7989P\"></sup> to cross the valley, but David and the other four hundred continued the pursuit.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>They found an Egyptian in a field and brought him to David. They gave him water to drink and food to eat—",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>part of a cake of pressed figs and two cakes of raisins. He ate and was revived,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7991Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7991Q\"></sup> for he had not eaten any food or drunk any water for three days and three nights.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>David asked him, “Who do you belong to? Where do you come from?”He said, “I am an Egyptian, the slave of an Amalekite.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7992R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7992R\"></sup> My master abandoned me when I became ill three days ago.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>We raided the Negev of the Kerethites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7993S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7993S\"></sup> some territory belonging to Judah and the Negev of Caleb.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7993T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7993T\"></sup> And we burned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7993U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7993U\"></sup> Ziklag.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>David asked him, “Can you lead me down to this raiding party?”He answered, “Swear to me before God that you will not kill me or hand me over to my master,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7994V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7994V\"></sup> and I will take you down to them.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He led David down, and there they were, scattered over the countryside, eating, drinking and reveling<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7995W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7995W\"></sup> because of the great amount of plunder<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7995X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7995X\"></sup> they had taken from the land of the Philistines and from Judah.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>David fought<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7996Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7996Y\"></sup> them from dusk until the evening of the next day, and none of them got away, except four hundred young men who rode off on camels and fled.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7996Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7996Z\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>David recovered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7997AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7997AA\"></sup> everything the Amalekites had taken, including his two wives.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Nothing was missing: young or old, boy or girl, plunder or anything else they had taken. David brought everything back.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He took all the flocks and herds, and his men drove them ahead of the other livestock, saying, “This is David’s plunder.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then David came to the two hundred men who had been too exhausted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8000AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8000AB\"></sup> to follow him and who were left behind at the Besor Valley. They came out to meet David and the men with him. As David and his men approached, he asked them how they were.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But all the evil men and troublemakers among David’s followers said, “Because they did not go out with us, we will not share with them the plunder we recovered. However, each man may take his wife and children and go.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>David replied, “No, my brothers, you must not do that with what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given us. He has protected us and delivered into our hands the raiding party that came against us.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Who will listen to what you say? The share of the man who stayed with the supplies is to be the same as that of him who went down to the battle. All will share alike.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8003AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8003AC\"></sup>”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>David made this a statute and ordinance for Israel from that day to this.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>When David reached Ziklag, he sent some of the plunder to the elders of Judah, who were his friends, saying, “Here is a gift<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8005AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8005AD\"></sup> for you from the plunder of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s enemies.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>David sent it to those who were in Bethel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8006AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8006AE\"></sup> Ramoth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8006AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8006AF\"></sup> Negev and Jattir;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8006AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8006AG\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>to those in Aroer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8007AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8007AH\"></sup> Siphmoth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8007AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8007AI\"></sup> Eshtemoa<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8007AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8007AJ\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>and Rakal; to those in the towns of the Jerahmeelites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8008AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8008AK\"></sup> and the Kenites;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8008AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8008AL\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>to those in Hormah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8009AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8009AM\"></sup> Bor Ashan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8009AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8009AN\"></sup> Athak",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>and Hebron;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8010AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8010AO\"></sup> and to those in all the other places where he and his men had roamed."
		},
		"31": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">31 </span>Now the Philistines fought against Israel; the Israelites fled before them, and many fell dead on Mount Gilboa.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8011B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8011B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The Philistines were in hot pursuit of Saul and his sons,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8012C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8012C\"></sup> and they killed his sons Jonathan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8012D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8012D\"></sup> Abinadab and Malki-Shua.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8012E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8012E\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The fighting grew fierce around Saul, and when the archers overtook him, they wounded<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8013F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8013F\"></sup> him critically.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Saul said to his armor-bearer, “Draw your sword and run me through,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8014G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8014G\"></sup> or these uncircumcised<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8014H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8014H\"></sup> fellows will come and run me through and abuse me.”But his armor-bearer was terrified and would not do it; so Saul took his own sword and fell on it.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When the armor-bearer saw that Saul was dead, he too fell on his sword and died with him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Saul and his three sons and his armor-bearer and all his men died<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8016I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8016I\"></sup> together that same day.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When the Israelites along the valley and those across the Jordan saw that the Israelite army had fled and that Saul and his sons had died, they abandoned their towns and fled. And the Philistines came and occupied them.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The next day, when the Philistines<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8018J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8018J\"></sup> came to strip the dead, they found Saul and his three sons fallen on Mount Gilboa.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>They cut off his head and stripped off his armor, and they sent messengers throughout the land of the Philistines to proclaim the news<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8019K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8019K\"></sup> in the temple of their idols and among their people.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8019L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8019L\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>They put his armor in the temple of the Ashtoreths<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8020M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8020M\"></sup> and fastened his body to the wall of Beth Shan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8020N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8020N\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When the people of Jabesh Gilead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8021O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8021O\"></sup> heard what the Philistines had done to Saul,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>all their valiant men<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8022P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8022P\"></sup> marched through the night to Beth Shan. They took down the bodies of Saul and his sons from the wall of Beth Shan and went to Jabesh, where they burned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8022Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8022Q\"></sup> them.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then they took their bones<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8023R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8023R\"></sup> and buried them under a tamarisk<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8023S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8023S\"></sup> tree at Jabesh, and they fasted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8023T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8023T\"></sup> seven days.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8023U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8023U\"></sup>"
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;